title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cook rhubarb with 1 quart of water.
Add sugar and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add juices and salt.
Freezes well.

title: spring strawberry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple. Add enough water to the juice to measure 2 cups. Bring to boil. Dissolve gelatin. Add a cup of cold water. Cool until thickened. Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Chill until set.

title: quick chicken-n-dumplins
directions: Cook chicken breasts in enough water to make 2 cans of broth with celery, salt and pepper.
Remove skin.
Dice chicken.
Put soup in saucepan.
Add 2 cans of broth and celery.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken.
Mix Bisquick, egg and milk for dumplins. Drop by spoonful into soup mixture.
Lower heat; simmer until dumplins are done.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Cook broccoli; drain well.
Cook celery and onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Combine soup, milk and cheese; stir in rice, broccoli, and celery mixture.
Turn into two 2-quart casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 12 to 16 servings (at least).

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup finely ground pecans in bottom of pan.
In a separate bowl, mix cake mix, eggs, oil and blackberry wine together.
Sprinkle the black raspberry jello into batter; pour into Bundt pan.
Check for doneness after 50 minutes.
If it is browning too quickly before that, put a piece of foil loosely over top.
Let cool 20 to 30 minutes, then turn onto a plate.
Make glaze.
Drizzle onto cake.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix crackers, oleo and sugar.
Use 3/4 of mixture and line 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk, orange juice and mandarin oranges.
Mix and pour into lined pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place croutons in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan, greased. Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over croutons.
Add cheese and sausage or ham. Refrigerate overnight.
Pour soup and 1/3 cup milk over top before baking at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: candy red hot applesauce
directions: Peel, core and chop apples into large chunks.
Place in pan and cover almost completely with water.
Cover pan and bring to a simmer over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until apples are tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and spoon out as much water as possible.
Add red hots and sugar, stir until dissolved.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serves 5 - 6.

title: sarah's vegetable casserole
directions: Cook, drain and set aside broccoli in a large bowl.
Add drained corn, onion and Cheddar cubes and toss together.

title: one dish chicken dinner
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and green beans in a large roast pan. Place chicken over potatoes, carrots and green beans.
Place can of tomatoes over top.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and can of tomato paste over top.
Add amount of water needed.
Cook at 450° for 1 hour or until chicken is ready.
When almost ready, add cornstarch dissolved in water around to have gravy.

title: southern pecan chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix brown sugar, white sugar and flour.
Add margarine to milk and mix.
Add vanilla, eggs, salt and nuts.
Mix well before making crust.
Bake at 350° in 10-inch pan.
Reduce to 325° after golden brown.
Filling will be slightly shaky when done.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and lay flat with 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese on each breast.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until done.

title: lavina fishel tesh's treacle pudding
directions: Chop the suet finely.
Beat the eggs.
Warm the treacle and mix all the ingredients to the consistency of porridge.
Butter and paper a shape.
Pour the pudding into it.
Cover with a buttered paper and steam for about 2 hours.

title: minute rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: flick-ette cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, salt and soda; blend into creamed mix.
Stir in flick-ettes. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 8 dozen.

title: new england pot roast
directions: In pot, brown roast on medium for 5 minutes each side; add salt and pepper.
Spread horseradish over; add water on side and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook for 1 additional hour.
(If done in oven use 350°.)

title: hershey's mini kiss peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening and peanut butter until well blended.
Add 1/3 cup granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add peanut butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in extra granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Immediately place 3 chocolate pieces on top of each cookie, pressing down slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Peel potatoes and cut average size.
Peel squash and cut size of potatoes.
Cut okra also to fry.
Mix together.
On top of stove, in big skillet with shortening about 1-inch deep, heat well and add vegetables, stirring them so all will be done (brown) at the same time.
Serve at once.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Put flour, salt and butter in bowl and mix together with fork. Add egg and water; mix by hand.
Roll out dough thin and cut with knife or pizza cutter.
Drop into boiling water and cook for 15 minutes.
Fry all cabbage with oil and water.
Add noodles and simmer; serve.

title: ice-cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a 13x9x2 dish for the amount of time instructed.
When thoroughly cooled, cut cake vertically in half (down the 9-inch side).
Now cut each half horizontally through the middle.
Layer all four pieces of cake on a cookie sheet and freeze until ready to use.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cut cabbage up and boil in salted water for 8 to 10 minutes. Drain.
Add 2/3 of cheese and other ingredients.
Toss lightly. Pour into buttered dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic apple-oatmeal bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream margarine, egg, vanilla and juice.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add apples, nuts and raisins. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Bring to boil oleo, water, cocoa, shortening and sugar and cocoa.
Pour over flour and beat well.
Add eggs, buttermilk cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Beat well until smooth.
Bake in 11 x 16-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lime pickles
directions: Wash and slice pickles in large container.
(Do not use aluminum.)
Mix 2 cups lime in 2 gallons water.
Pour over pickles.
Let set 24 hours.
Rinse in 4 different changes of water.
Cover with cold water and let soak 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.

title: mexican-american tacos
directions: Mix hamburger with chili powder and saute.
Breaking meat up, brown 5 minutes.
Stir in beans and bean liquid, catsup, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat while you fix tortillas.
Place tortillas on cookie sheet.
Spread with melted butter.
Place in hot oven (400°) until they soften.
Spoon in 1/2 cup of chili mixture; fold in half.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes (longer if you have trouble keeping the tacos folded).
Be sure they are well buttered before filling and folding, and place a knife over them to keep them weighted down.

title: shrimp and crab madeira
directions: Melt butter.
Add shallots and saute until soft.
Add mushrooms and saute until liquid evaporates.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add crab.
Stir in Madeira and cook until almost reduced.
Add tarragon, lemon juice and tomato paste.
Mix. Combine yolks and cream and very slowly add to saucepan, mixing constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Taste and correct seasoning. Serve on linguine topped with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: mexicali rice
directions: In medium saucepan, brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, pepper, mustard, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt and rice.
Mix well.
Cover pan and over low heat, cook down until rice is tender and dish is thick (15 to 20 minutes).
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken marsala(italian)
directions: Flour cutlets. Saute sliced garlic in oil.
When browned, remove and brown cutlets.
Mix remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup water and pour over cutlets.

title: southwest spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Whisk together the milk and egg and mix in the hot pasta.
Spread the mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook the pork, onion, green pepper and garlic together in a large skillet for about 6 minutes over medium heat until pork is cooked through.
Drain excess fat.
Stir chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt and black pepper into the pork and cook for about 2 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce and cook 2 minutes more.
Spread meat over pasta in baking dish.
Sprinkle both cheeses evenly over top.
Bake in lower third of oven for about 10 minutes, until cheese is melted and casserole begins to bubble.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: potato chowder
directions: Heat milk just hot.
In a pan, melt butter and saute onions; do not brown.
Add flour to butter and onions; blend well.
Add milk to flour and onions; let come to a boil while stirring.
In saucepan, put potatoes, celery and carrots and cover with chicken stock or water (just barely cover vegetables).
Bring to a boil and simmer until tender.
Add vegetables to the cream sauce. Season with salt and pepper.
Ladle into bowls and garnish with the green onion tops and parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced apple cake
directions: Bake cake according to mix recipe in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix condensed milk, sour cream and lemon juice.
Pour over warm cake. Bake additional 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and stir together. Mix the instant pudding.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Slice cucumber rings in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Remove the seeds.
Add water and salt to cucumbers and let stand 5 days. Drain.
Combine 1 cup vinegar, alum and food coloring; pour over cucumbers in kettle and cover to the top of cucumbers with water. Simmer for 2 hours; drain.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin until tender.
Peel and slice thinly into bowl. Fry bacon until crisp and reserve fat.
Cool potatoes and add 1/3 cup bacon fat in a skillet until potatoes are yellow. Add sliced yellow onion.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine
Crisco,
sugar
and
boiling water and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in the 1 cup of lukewarm water, then add this and the beaten egg to the first mixture.
Mix in the salt, soda,
baking powder and flour.
Use the regular method of mixing for bread.
Place dough in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and cook over low heat until well blended.
Add 2 cups hot chicken stock and the warm milk and cream.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until thick.
Add remaining 4 cups of the chicken stock and chicken and heat to boiling.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter, egg and pecans.
Press evenly in bottom and sides of 8 x 12-inch baking sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda in a bowl.
Melt margarine, cocoa and water; simmer for 2 minutes.
Pour over mixture in
bowl, stir and add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake on a greased and floured sheet pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine sugar and 2 1/2 cups water in saucepan.
Put on the heat until sugar is dissolved; cool.
Add frozen lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Blend thoroughly and chill. Pour juice over the sherbet.
Mix and serve.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together well.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover with sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Yield:
12 to 16 balls.

title: quick fudge
directions: Heat chips and milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: strawberry chiffon squares
directions: Melt margarine and stir in crushed wafers.
Put firmly in 2-quart shallow dish.
Chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix together rest of ingredients except butter and cinnamon until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Pour cinnamon and butter over all the top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cookies
directions: Warm milk (don't boil) until bubbles form.
Add tea bags; when cool squeeze tea bags and discard.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add butter and work until sandy texture.
Make a well in center, add milk.
Blend until smooth.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Roll out on floured surface (1/4-inch thick).
Cut with cutters.
Bake at 350° until lightly golden (12 to 15 minutes). Enjoy!

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix milk, margarine, cocoa
and
sugar together and let boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from
heat and add oats and peanut butter. Spoon by teaspoon onto cookie sheet; let cool and put in cookie jar.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add margarine and chocolate mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour a 9-inch pie pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: flaky oil pie pastry
directions: In medium bowl, mix with fork all ingredients until texture of coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle 3 to 4 tablespoons of cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, into flour mixture.
Mix lightly with fork after each addition until pastry is moist.
Divide pastry evenly. Dampen countertop with water.
Place piece of waxed paper, about 12 square-inches, on surface.
Put half of dough on this.
Cover with a second piece of waxed paper.
Roll out dough until about 1-inch larger in circumference than pie pan.
Remove top waxed paper. Place pie pan face down on dough.
Quickly flip dough over by grasping bottom waxed paper, 1 hand opposite the other.
Slowly peel off waxed paper and ease crust into pan.
Crust will break easily but it also patches easy and doesn't show like normal crusts.
Repeat rolling technique for top crust.
Peel off top paper, then carefully flip top crust onto pie.
Be sure to seal crusts well with prongs of fork.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar, eggs and salad oil.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, diced apples, walnuts and vanilla.
Combine dry mixture with sugar mixture and beat.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In colander, mix zucchini and salt.
Let drain about 15 minutes, squeezing out excess liquid with back of spoon.
Mix well drained zucchini (about 1 cup), carrot, onion, parsley, egg, flour and pepper.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cover bottom of dish with dried beef. Wrap bacon around chicken and place in Pyrex dish.
Mix sour cream, soup and Worcestershire sauce and pour over chicken. Cover with foil.
Cook 2 hours at 300°.
Great with rice.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit together.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not mix.
Top with fruit and juice.
Do not stir. Bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Add 8 ounces La Creme Cool Whip after removing from refrigerator. Spread mixture over cake layers.
Let stand in refrigerator 4 days before eating.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add ingredients to whip cream to desired taste.
Refrigerate. Good with various fruits.

title: black bean skillet
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients in large skillet.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 12 to 14 minutes.
Stir in can of tomato soup.
Heat through.
Stir in almonds.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve with bread and salad.
Serves 4.

title: tallahassee hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add milk and water.
Stir in chopped onion.
Add more meal or milk if necessary to make a soft, but workable, dough.
Mold into pones about 5 inches long and 3 inches wide, and about 3/4-inch thick.
Fry in hot deep fat or oil (365°) until well browned.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli, onion, celery and carrot.
In a saucepan, put broccoli and cover with water; bring to a boil and simmer.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add onion, celery, carrot and bouillon to broccoli.

title: shortcakes
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Knife in soft margarine; add milk.
Roll on floured surface to 1/2-inch thick. Using a large glass, cut circles out.
Bake at 450° on lightly greased pan until golden brown.
Top with your favorite fruit.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all together; add boiling water last.
Bake in tube pan or two loaf pans at 350° until cake tests done.
Put lemon sauce on top.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: Combine all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend together until dough is smooth.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon of dough onto hot pizzelle iron.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 dozen.

title: seafood jambalaya
directions: Saut green pepper, onions and celery in butter.
Add pepper and garlic.
Place in slow cooker.
Add tomatoes, gumbo fil, hot peppers and sausages; cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in bay leaves, okra, shrimp and crab legs.
Cook 1 to 2 hours longer until done.
Pour over rice on large platter.

title: peach in a cloud
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients for 2 minutes and pour into pie plate.
Drain peaches (save juice).
Spread peaches in center of pie plate (keep about 1-inch from edge).
Mix together until smooth 3 tablespoons peach juice with cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar. Spoon on top until peaches are covered.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before slicing, then refrigerate.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in pot; add onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain
oil.
Add
all
other ingredients;	cook until bell pepper and celery melt away.

title: san diego chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and red pepper; cook 3 to 4 minutes until soft.
Add mushrooms, 1/2 cup of wine, garlic and tomato paste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Season about 1 1/2 cups of flour to lightly coat both sides of chicken.
In a large, heavy saucepan or Dutch oven, heat remaining 1 tablespoon of oil.
Cook chicken for 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Add the cooked veggies to saucepot of chicken; stir in basil, chicken broth and remaining 1/2 cup red wine.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: pineapple beans with meatballs
directions: Combine beef, onion and salt; mix well and form into 1-inch balls.
Brown well in oil; drain.

title: yams and apples
directions: Place yams and apples in layers in casserole dish.
Heat and thicken remaining ingredients.
Pour over yams and bake 45 minutes or until apples are tender at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, adding the corn muffin mix last.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to one hour, until golden brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour into a jelly roll pan that has been greased.
Spread batter into the corners.
Bake for 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Loosen cake from edges of the pan.
Flip the cake onto wax paper and roll.
Place in freezer while filling is being prepared.

title: mushroom pie
directions: Drain mushrooms and save liquid.
Melt butter and half and half to make 2 cups.
Stir in.
Add salt, pepper and sauteed onions.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add mushrooms and pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: witch's brew
directions: Brown burger and bacon, drain.
Add pepper and onions until slightly cooked.
Add rest of ingredients and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stir-fry beef and vegetables
directions: Toss beef in a bowl with soy sauce and sherry.
Cover and marinate for 30 minutes.
Prepare vegetables.
Set aside.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes; stir in salt.
Add ice cubes.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Add cubes as needed.
Cukes will be crisp and cold. Drain. Add onions.

title: salad
directions: Peel oranges and free the sections from the membrane.
Remove seeds.
Cut sections in halves crosswise.
Lay on bed of lettuce leaves and serve with French dressing.
Sprinkle with tarragon or with minced green pepper, if desired; Diced celery can also be used.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Prepare shells as directed on package.

title: spinach cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients into drained spinach.
Freeze in individual mounds (ice cream scoop).
When ready to thaw, place on thick slice of tomato.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° (30 minutes if frozen).
Serves 16.

title: spiced applesauce drops
directions: Cream shortening. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Use 1/2 cup to mix with dates and nuts.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce to egg mixture.
Stir in floured fruit and nut mixture.
Drop from teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until top springs back under fingertip pressure, about 15 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Boil rice in the water with bouillon cubes.
Combine oil, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over hot cooked rice.
Mix together eggs, celery, dill pickle, pimiento, mayonnaise, onion, mustard and olives.
Add to warm rice.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Let cheese soften; mash up with fork.
Puree pimento.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
The pimento cheese is better if made a day ahead.
If stiff when ready to use, add mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon at a time, to make mixture easy to spread.

title: rosa's (murdock) rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Melt shortening but save to add last (shortening will kill the yeast).
Add sugar, buttermilk and half of the flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Add shortening and more flour until you can handle it.
Grease hands and roll any size you wish.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: batter bread
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and mix well.
Sift into this the meal, salt and baking powder.
Add boiling water and beat thoroughly. Pour mixture into hot pan and bake at 450° until very brown, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: american chop suey
directions: Form sausage into small balls and brown.
Saute celery and onions.
Mix together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 300°.

title: hobo dinner on the outdoor grill
directions: Mix onion soup mix and hamburger thoroughly.
Form into 4 patties.
Cut aluminum foil in squares big enough to hold 1 patty, sliced carrot and potatoes (and 1 large slice onion, if desired).

title: vegetable corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch round baking pan; set aside.
Combine cornmeal, flour and sugar.
Add milk, butter and egg.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in zucchini and roasted red pepper. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.

title: vegetable dip from dallas, texas
directions: Heat tomato and Jell-O together until Jell-O dissolves.
Cool. In a separate bowl, cream together cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add the cooled soup mixture and blend together.

title: quick rolls or raised biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda, then cut in Crisco shortening and the buttermilk to the yeast mixture.
Mix all ingredients well.
Dough will be stiff.
Turn out on well floured surface.
Knead about 20 times with hands.
Roll out and cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place in pan.
Cover with moist tea towel and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brush with melted margarine.
Serve while warm.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham
cracker crumbs and one melted stick of oleo. Press into
Pyrex dish or 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, remaining oleo and egg.
Beat 15 minutes.
Pour over cracker crumbs. Slice bananas
over
cake mixture, add pineapple and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle
with
nuts
and
cherries,
chill before serving.

title: cushaw cake
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients together. Add eggs, oil, cushaw and mix well. Add vanilla and pecans and mix. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend until all of flour is moistened.
Can make 3 or 4 pie crusts.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place marshmallows on hot cake.
They should melt slightly.
Cool and frost.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and spread with melted margarine. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole and set aside.
Cook sausage and drain.
Crumble sausage and spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Combine cream or milk, eggs and salt.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: perfectly easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine the warm water and yeast in a large bowl. Let the mixture stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes. Stir in butter, sugar, salt and eggs. Beat in flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough is too stiff to mix (some flour may not be needed). Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or up to 4 days.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt, sugar, egg and oil; mix well.
Add flour, 1/2 at a time.
Mix well.
Place in greased bowl and cover with foil.
Place in refrigerator.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt in double boiler the caramel, butter and water.
Add nut halves.
Drop by tablespoons onto buttered tray to cool.
Mix in double boiler the chocolate bar and wax; stir until smooth.
Dip caramel patties in chocolate and place on waxed paper to dry.

title: quick delicious shake
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Add egg white or several ice cubes for a frothy shake.
Makes 2 shakes.

title: spanakopita
directions: Wash spinach and drain thoroughly.
Chop finely with onions. Beat eggs well.
Add with cheese to spinach in a large bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix with other ingredients, except cheese and crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture after it has been placed in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Line 18 to 24 muffin cups with paper liners.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, nutmeg, water, oil and egg; mix well. Spoon into prepared muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: falafel
directions: In a large bowl, mix the beans, potatoes and tahini.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on a nonstick baking sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic and sugar.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Prepare 8 ounce package of egg noodles as directed.
Mix together green onions, sour cream and cream cheese.
Grease a casserole dish.
Add 1/2 noodles; spread 1/2 meat on noodles, then 1/2 cream cheese mixture. Repeat.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop taco casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil; place in 11 x 14-inch pan.
Pour rice around chops.
Mix water, tomato sauce, taco mix and 1 teaspoon salt.
Pour over chops and rice.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: mom's dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by tablespoon in broth, gravy or stews.
Let cook 20 minutes.
Cover pan.
Do not uncover kettle for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: In large skillet, combine shrimp, wine, lemon juice and lime juice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer covered 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except linguine.
Cook, stirring constantly, just until snow peas are tender and shrimp is opaque, about 5 minutes.

title: texas pralines (microwave style)
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together in microwave bowl and cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 12 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Immediately drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered foil.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Cook together and strain the cranberries and 1 quart water. Cook together cloves, red hots, 1 quart water and 2 cups sugar until red hots melt.
Mix these mixtures together with frozen lemonade and orange juice (small cans).
Add 3 quarts water. Serve hot.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Put liquid in large percolator.
Put spices in basket. Percolate and serve hot.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: blueberry-banana delight
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Cream with sugar.
Whip the cream with 1 cup sugar.
Add cream cheese mixture to prepared whipped cream.
Slice bananas and layer in pie shells.
Pour whipped mixture over bananas.
Top with prepared blueberry pie filling. Makes 2 pies.

title: icing for prune cake
directions: Bring ingredients to a full boil, boil 2 minutes.
Pour over top and sides of cake.
Let soak in.

title: beer brined chicken with giblet gravy
directions: Combine the apple cider, brown sugar, salt, peppercorns, juniper berries, bay leaves, cinnamon, and cloves in a large pot or bowl. Stir to dissolve the sugar and salt.

Combine the mixture with the beer in a plastic container. Place the chicken in the brine and, if necessary, weigh down with a heavy dinner plate to completely submerge. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: dinner - the easy way
directions: Call pizza place that delivers.
Use coupons if you have them. Order pizza(s) of choice.
Find checkbook while waiting for delivery.

title: recipe for life
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of sorrow, joy and sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten others and raise the texture for great heights of Christian living.

title: spicy broccoli dip
directions: Place broccoli in 1-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 5 to 7 minutes, or until tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time to break apart; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat, covered, on full power for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes, or until heated through.
Stir halfway through heating time.
May be served hot with crackers.

title: indonesian sate (satay)
directions: You will need 20 to 25 bamboo skews (small or medium).

title: taco roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on soft flour taco shells.
Roll and cut into 1 inch sections.
Serve with salsa.

title: noel's favorite welsh scones
directions: Pastry blend flour, salt and butter.
Add sugar, soda and cream of tartar.
Beat eggs with milk; add to flour mixture.
Turn out on floured board.
Pat 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into favorite shapes.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Bake 8 minutes at 450°.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine flour and beer.
Cover bowl and let sit for no less than 3 hours.
Slice onions in 1/4-inch slices.
Dip in batter and fry.
Drain on brown paper bag on jelly roll pan and keep in warm oven while frying others.
Can be frozen.
Reheat in 450° oven.

title: lemon sponge dessert
directions: Heat milk and butter together and slowly pour over beaten egg yolks. Add sugar, salt and flour which have been thoroughly mixed. Add lemon juice and rind and fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in buttered custard cups (8 or 9), set in hot water, 45 minutes at 350°. Turn out when cold. Serve upside down with whipped cream. Will keep several days in the refrigerator.
Serves 8 or 9.

title: egg noodles with smoked chicken and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is translucent (10 minutes). Increase heat to medium-high. Add mushrooms and salt and cook, stirring, until the mushrooms are well browned (7 minutes). Reduce heat to medium-low and stir in the flour (1 minute). Add broth, paprika and mustard. Reduce heat to low and simmer until sauce thickens (3 minutes). Stir in chicken and cook 1 minute.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook until raisins are tender and water is gone.
Blend in applesauce, eggs, Sweet*10, oil, cinnamon, vanilla, nutmeg, flour and raisins last.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops off bell peppers and clean out seeds.
Cook in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Drain and chop tomatoes, reserving juice. Combine beef, rice, drained tomatoes, onions, seasonings and egg.
Mix well. Stuff peppers with meat mixture. Place upright in buttered baking dish.
Blend reserved tomato juice, bouillon cubes and water.
Pour around peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, then pour following mixture over it and toss lightly until covered.

title: corn and potato chowder(microwave)
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Combine bacon and onion in 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 10 to 13 minutes or until bacon is thoroughly cooked and onion is tender. Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in large baking dish.
Spread soup over chicken. Mix eggs, milk, onion and stuffing together.
Spread over soup. Pour 3 cups broth over this and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients until smooth and spread in pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pecans in shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until center is firm to touch.
Serves 8.

title: summer salad
directions: Wash, drain and prepare all vegetables.
Blend sour cream, sesame seed, garlic and cheese mix.
Allow to sit overnight.
Toss salad dressing with mixed vegetables.

title: tomato skillet cabbage
directions: In medium skillet, heat reserved tomato juice and bouillon until bouillon is dissolved. Stir in cabbage; cover tightly.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle uncooked rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put uncooked chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix soups, water and milk.
Pour over chicken and rice. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend dry biscuit mix and milk; roll about 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Mix ground beef, chopped onion, salt and 1/4 can of beef gravy.
Spread this mixture on the rolled out dough.
Roll up as a "log" and cut 8 or 9 slices.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Heat rest of gravy and pour over cooked and cut slices.
Serves approximately 4 people.

title: aunt kate's blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift flour, powder and add to creamed mix, beating well.
Roll one quart berries in a little flour and stir into the batter.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together all ingredients except onions and tomatoes until well blended. Spoon into shallow ovenproof dish or 9-inch pie plate. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned. Sprinkle with onion and tomato. Serve with Triscuits or toasted bread cutouts. Makes 2 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes on 350°.

title: martha co. casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown ground beef in the butter, salt and tomato sauce.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, onion, green pepper and cream cheese.
Put the noodles in a casserole dish; then add the cream cheese mixture.
Then add the beef mixture on top.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Combine spices and sauce in bowl.
Pour 1/2 of sauce over meat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add corn to meat mixture.

title: dark chocolate frosting 4
directions: Mix melted butter and cocoa, add salt, then add 4x sugar, milk and vanilla extract.
Enough to frost 2 big 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: spiced pear salad(makes 8 servings)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet or wide saucepan, combine brown sugar, orange juice, vinegar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add pear halves.
Cover and simmer 5 to 6 minutes, or until pears are tender.
Remove from heat.
Transfer pears carefully to a storage dish and pour poaching liquid over them.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: satin eggs
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add milk and salt and beat. Rub butter around inside of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water for 20 minutes.

title: economy punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add Kool-Aid and juice and chill. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serve in punch bowl with ice cubes.
Serves approximately 35.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients gently.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar when done.

title: salisbury steak bake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with ingredients. Shape into 6 patties. Place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour off fat. Mix remaining soup with 1/2 cup water. Pour over patties and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine onion, pepper, eggs, milk, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper together.
Mix well.
Combine ground beef and sausage meat, mixing well.
Add egg mixture to meat mixture, combining well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and place in bowl to cool.
Heat barbecue sauce over medium heat for 10 minutes; pour in wine and let simmer.
If sauce separates, add more barbecue sauce.
Pour sauce over meatballs and heat before serving.

title: fruit delight
directions: Drain all fruit.
Add pack of vanilla instant pudding.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix. Bring to boil, stirring all the time.
Lower heat and cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 tablespoon butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Beat until begins to thicken. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Enjoy!

title: potato, cheese, ham casserole
directions: Line bottom of one greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with layer of potatoes.
Cover with layer of onions and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Next, sprinkle with grated cheese and then ham (chopped or ground).
Repeat layers until ham is top layer.

title: grandma's orange cookies
directions: *If you don't have any buttermilk or sour milk on hand, add a little vinegar to whole milk to turn it sour.
Buttermilk is best.

title: mom's strawberry freezer jam
directions: Combine sugar and strawberries.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir Sure-Jell into water; bring to a boil and boil rapidly for 1 minute. Stir constantly.
Remove from stove.
Add berries and stir 2 minutes. Pour into jelly jars. Cover and let stand at room temperature until jellied.
This may take 2 hours or even 2 days.
Seal with paraffin (I don't) and store in freezer.
Makes great ice cream topping.
Peaches can be used in place of strawberries to make a peach jam.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cut tops off peppers.
Clean peppers and stuff with cheese. Divide sausage into 6 or 8 pieces.
Pat a patty in your hand and lay pepper in middle.
Wrap meat all around pepper
and roll in bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in rice and raisins.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes; stir.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy taco bean soup
directions: In soup kettle, brown sausage and beef over medium heat, drain.
Stir in water and taco seasoning, powdered ranch.
Drain and rinse all beans.
Do not drain and rinse mexican tomatoes and diced tomatoes.
Add all remaining ingredients in kettle. Bring to boil and reduce heat, simmer uncovered for about 30 minutes. Stirring occasionally.
Yields 13 14 servings.
For milder taste, use milder sausage or salsa or leave out tomatoes with green chilies.

title: mexican beef stew
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, cook beef, onion and garlic powder until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat. Add soup, beef broth, water, potatoes and chili powder. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover; cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Add corn and heat through, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cheese. If desired, garnish with green onion. Serves 6.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake.) Cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten while cooling.
Cool slightly, remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sherried mushroom patties
directions: Bake shells according to package directions.
Remove center of shells when cool enough to handle; set aside.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add sour cream,
Parmesan cheese, sherry and garlic powder.
Cook over low heat until warmed.
Serve in shells; garnish with parsley.
Prepare just before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Open can of tomatoes and chicken broth and set aside. These ingredients have to be added quickly, so have them ready.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Mix thoroughly the 1 cup cake mix, sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Sprinkle over the top of pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Let stand until cool.
Cut in squares.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: corn chowder
directions: Heat salt pork in a frypan to release fat.
Then saute onions in the pan.
When they are soft, add potatoes and boiling water. Simmer until potatoes are soft and then stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat the soup through and serve.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into buttered baking dish.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar and cinnamon in water in a saucepan.
Add peanuts; boil on medium heat until all syrup has been absorbed, stirring frequently.
Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Separate with fork.
Bake in oven at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together the corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Add onions, buttermilk and water.
Mix well. Add butter and egg and blend.
Drop by small tablespoons into preheated butter.
Cook until golden brown.
Yields about 30.

title: date nut cake
directions: Pour 1/2 cup hot water with 1 teaspoon of soda over the 2 cups chopped dates.
Meanwhile, cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beaten, one at a time with the shortening and sugar.
Sift the flour and stir in the nuts.
Add date mixture, milk and dry ingredients alternately with the sugar and shortening mixture. Bake for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add to browned hamburger, peppers and onion. Stir in soups along with Velveeta from box of macaroni.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in oleo until light brown. Cut up tomatoes and put in Pyrex casserole dish.
Add sauteed onions.
Sprinkle Mrs. Dash over tomatoes.
Melt about 1/2 cube of oleo in saucepan.
Add torn up bread.
When coated good, put on top of tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and bread is sort of toasted on top.

title: lime pie
directions: Place milk in freezer tray.
Place in freezer until frozen 1/2 inch around edges.
While freezing milk, dissolve jello in boiling water.
When slightly cooled, add sugar, lemon juice and peel. Put milk in large mixing bowl and beat until thick.
Pour over lime mixture and beat.
Add a few drops green food coloring if desired.
Pour into crust and chill several hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Skin chicken.
Cook chicken.
Let it cool. Pick it off the bones.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Just use the top of the broccoli.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Chop onion and mango.
Brown in skillet.
Add corned beef, catsup and chili sauce.
Cook until thick enough for sandwiches.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Heat applesauce and stir soda into applesauce when it is taken off stove.
Stir into mixture and then fold in dry ingredients which have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Batter will keep one week.
Makes 3 dozen small or 1 dozen larger muffins.

title: mrs. baggett's light fruit cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Beat separately the yolks and whites of eggs.
Add yolks to creamed mixture.
Add nutmeg, mace and wine.
Add egg whites last.
In another bowl, add flour and baking powder and add this to chopped fruit and nuts. Stir until all are well coated, then add first mixture.
Mix well. Place in paper lined cake pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or less.

title: brown rice
directions: Grease dish with margarine.
Mix rice, soup, onions and bell pepper in dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 50 minutes. Cut oven off, take rice out of oven, loosen with fork.
Cover again with foil and place in oven again.
Leave until oven cools. Serves 7.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place pieces of cooked chicken (or turkey leftovers) into greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk together.
Spread stuffing mix on top of chicken; pour soup and milk mixture on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: glazed grilled salmon
directions: Combine brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and soy sauce in medium bowl; whisk to blend.
Transfer 1 Tbsp. glaze to small bowl.
Brush one side of salmon steak generously with half of the glaze.
Place salmon steaks, glazed side down onto barbeque grill (medium to high heat).
Grill until glaze is slightly charred, about four minutes. Brush topside of salmon with remaining glaze.
Turn salmon over and grill until second side is slightly charred and salmon is just opaque in center, about five minutes longer.
Transfer salmon to plate and drizzle with one Tbsp of reserved glaze and serve.

title: nag shead pudding
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar.
Pour mixture into Cool Whip.
Slice bananas and add bananas and crushed pineapple.
Whip or stir into a smooth mixture.
Layer glass dish with vanilla wafers.
Pour in mixture.
Garnish top with chopped nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: preacher's rolls(an appropriate recipe for this book)
directions: My grandfather was nicknamed "Preacher" because his father was a United Methodist minister.
At any family gathering, Preacher would always make the rolls.
Just before he died, he asked me to come watch him so that I could carry on the family tradition.
I guess he knew his time with us was short.
Here is a beloved family recipe with Preacher's hints.

title: shrimp ring
directions: Dissolve cream cheese in undiluted soup over low heat.
Add pepper, onion and celery.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 tablespoon cold water and add to soup mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour into mold.
Chill overnight.

title: mushroom and onions for over steaks
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender. Serve hot over steak or hamburgers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients with enough flour just so you can handle it.
Roll out to about 3/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle sugar on top and cut out with cookie cutter.
Put a raisin on top of each cookie.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
These are good, rich, soft sugar cookies.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break in large pieces into mixing bowl. Beat eggs with milk, sugar and cinnamon. Pour over bread. Mix well. Pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: Place margarine in cast-iron skillet.
Place in 400° oven for 3 to 5 minutes or until melted.

title: hot pepper jelly(jalapeno)
directions: Add salt to ground peppers and let stand for 4 hours; drain. Add sugar, vinegar and butter; bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Take off heat and add Jell-O.
Skim and put in jar.

title: chili
directions: Cook on medium heat for about 2 hours.

title: coconut cream eggs
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Slowly add powdered sugar and coconut.
Shape and chill.
If mix is too moist to shape, slowly add a little more powdered sugar.
Coat chilled eggs with chocolate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, orange peel, and vanilla.
Add egg, beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients, blend in.
Divide dough into 1/2. Chill one hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef with taco mix; drain grease.
Layer in 2 (1 1/2-quart) casserole dishes.
Start with cheese, meat, onion, pepper, green chilies and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix up everything.
When it's done, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Tabasco sauce (if desired) and/or garlic salt and cheese on top.
Microwave on High 20 minutes.

title: sweet-potato puffs
directions: Cook potatoes until tender (20 minutes or so); drain well. Cool slightly.
Mash.
In a medium bowl, combine.
Refrigerate for awhile if too soft.
This is how I do it!!

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken.
Bone chicken.
Use 1/2 of stuffing in the bottom of a baking dish.
Pour chicken broth over stuffing to moisten stuffing.
Spread chicken on top of stuffing.

title: jan's gooey bars
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, nuts and butter or margarine.
Put in a 9 X 13 pan.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Cook until hard boil. Remove from burner and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn and bake 1 or 2 hours on 2 cookie sheets.

title: drumstick treat
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, 2/3 cup peanuts and margarine together. Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: dill pickles("first prize winner")
directions: You will need 4 quart jars.

title: souperburger sandwiches
directions: Brown beef and onion together until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup, mustard and pepper and simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Serve on buns with slaw.

title: mixed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Right before serving, add salt, pepper, oil and vinegar to taste.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add oil, eggs and 7-Up.
Mix well. Pour into
large
layer pans (paper in bottom and greased). Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa into a large bowl.
Cream oil, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs; add color to this.
Combine buttermilk and soda; add to oil mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and vanilla; mix well.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Bring 1/2 cup sugar and milk to boil; spoon over cooled cake before frosting with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix mushroom soup, evaporated milk and enchilada sauce.
Spread meat on flour tortilla.
Spoon on sauce mixture and add cheese.
Roll up.
Fix all mixtures in tortillas and layer in baking dish.
Top with sauce mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with foil when baking.
Serve with sour cream.

title: almond skillet coffee cake(a family favorite!  always a hit!)
directions: Melt margarine and add to sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour, salt and flavoring. Mix well.
Pour batter into a large iron skillet that has been lined in heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Be sure to oil the foil to prevent sticking.
Cover the batter with sliced almonds and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let this set until cool.

title: parmesan butter pan biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter and set aside.
Combine all ingredients except the milk and butter.
Stir in milk until moist. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 10 times until smooth.
Roll into 12 x 4-inch rectangle and cut into 12 (1-inch) strips.
Dip into butter and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 2 rows of 6.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl.
Float Ice Ring on top, if desired.

title: alabama sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients and turn into a pastry lined pie plate.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until crust is brown.

title: sweet & sour chicken wings
directions: Cut off an discard wing tips (may be saved for soup).
Cut remaining portion in two parts.
Salt each chicken wing and roll in cornstarch.
Dip in beaten eggs and brown in oil in a skillet. Dissolve bouillon cube in water; combine with catsup, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce.
Pour over chicken wings which are arranged in one layer in a flat, shallow casserole.
Cover with foil; bake 325° for 45 minutes, then uncover pan and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: sauce for pasta
directions: Drain marinade from artichoke hearts into a skillet. Coarsely chop artichokes.
In skillet saut mushrooms in hot marinade.
Add artichokes plus rest of ingredients except pasta. Simmer, uncovered, approximately 15 - 20 minutes.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onion until color changes (around 5 minutes).
Add soup, sour cream and carrots; stir until blended. Melt margarine; add to stuffing mix.
Divide mixture in half. Pour 1/2 in casserole dish.
Add zucchini mixture.
Pour remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, oleo and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and chips.
Add Marshmallow Creme until the fudge is as creamy as you like.
Makes a large amount.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Put onions, peppers and remaining ingredients in double boiler and stir until cheese has melted.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs until well beaten, add sugar and crisco, beat until creamy. Add vanilla and dry ingredients, beat till well mixed. Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet; sprinkle sugar on top of each one. Bake in 400° oven for 10 min.
Remove with spatula, cool completely before storing.
Yield 40 cookies.

title: chocolate punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and bake in jelly roll pan.
Cut in 1-inch cubes.
Mix instant pudding as directed.
Layer in large bowl the cake, pudding, Cool Whip, candy and chips.
Make a few layers, ending with chips.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing, sugar and vinegar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Place peach slices in a bowl.
Add sugar and Grand Marnier. Marinate peaches for 1 hour.
May need to add more Grand Marnier and sugar, depending on how sweet you like the peaches.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese, lettuce and croutons, in large bowl. Mix with whisk.
Add lettuce, sprinkle Parmesan and croutons and mix right before serving.

title: dreamsicle cookie mix
directions: Empty cookie mix into a large mixing bowl and stir to combine. Add 3/4 cup softened butter, 1 egg slightly beaten, and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Mix until completely blended.
If dough is too dry, stir in just enough milk or water to make cookie dough mixture.
Roll heaping tablespoons into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12 to 14 minutes or until tops are very lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
YIELD:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: instant russian tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup boiling water.
Great for gift giving!

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except cinnamon) with electric mixer or blender.
Pour into pie crust; sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes or until set and inserted knife comes out clean.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Mix ingredients together and serve with dressing.

title: italian beef with peppers
directions: Place roast on foil; arrange bay leaves and garlic slices on and around the meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Insert meat thermometer in thickest part.
Seal foil and place in roasting pan.
Roast at 325° to medium rare.
Cool and refrigerate overnight, saving pan juices.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Butter a 9 x 13 pan.
Add to thawed potatoes, soup, sour cream and seasonings.
Put half of potato mix in pan. Sprinkle half the cheese over top and add remaining potato mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Add remaining cheese on top and bake 15 minutes until brown.
May add ham chunks.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine; mix with all other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This is wonderful!

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: In a saucepan, mix orange juice, brown sugar, cloves and ginger.
Mix cornstarch and water to make a smooth paste and add to the mixture.
Stir until it thickens; add raisins and pour over ham and bake.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix and pour into 13x9-inch pan.
Bake 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Put carrots in greased casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients. Top with buttered crumbs.
Place in oven at 325° until bubbly.

title: ham broccoli chowder
directions: Cook onion, broccoli and potatoes in 2 cups water until tender.
Do not drain.
Add other ingredients, except half and half.
On low heat, cook until cheese is melted.
Add half and half.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick a few times with a fork and bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until soft.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato carefully.
Scoop out the pulp. Put in a bowl.
Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks to potato pulp. Stir and blend until smooth.
Add butter and cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: cabbage rolls (sarme)
directions: Boil cabbage in hot water 8-10 minutes.
Drain.
Peel off leaves.
Fry fat, onions, and garlic together until light brown. Mix with raw meat, rice, eggs, and spices.
Put 2 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of leaf and roll it up tight.
Put sauerkraut on bottom of large pan.
Arrange cabbage rolls on that. Pour tomato juice over all.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Serve with sour cream.

title: california garden casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir ground beef, onion, green pepper and celery in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown; drain.
Stir in noodles, sauce mix and water.
Heat to boiling; pour into ungreased dish, 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inches or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Arrange tomato slice on beef mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes.

title: county fair casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain. Combine ground beef, onion and seasonings in heavy saucepan. Stir in sour cream and soup.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in macaroni. Spoon mixture into casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and dry mustard.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg and milk mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Make day before and refrigerate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce in bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl. Layer peas, chopped pepper, chopped onion and chopped celery. Cover completely with thinly sliced cucumber.
Cover cucumber with Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Best if let set several hours or overnight.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Cream crabmeat and cream cheese together.
Add lemon juice, curry powder and Worcestershire sauce to your taste.
Add onion. Put in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Spread on crackers or whatever you like.

title: kahlua dessert
directions: Mix milk and Kahlua.

Dunk cookies into this and layer on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread on layer of Cool Whip, then layer of ice cream. Dunk another layer of cookies and place on top of the ice cream. Frost with Cool Whip.
Freeze. Serve frozen.

title: rhubarb streusel cake
directions: Mix butter, 1 1/2 cup sugar, eggs, 3 cups flour, baking powder, milk, vanilla, salt and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Mixture will be thick and stiff. Spread half the batter into a well buttered 9 X 13 pan. Mix the rhubarb, 1/2 cup sugar and jello. Spread over batter in pan. Combine 1/4 cup each of the flour, sugar, brown sugar, nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over rhubarb. Put rest of batter over the rhubarb, cinnamon and sugar mixture. Smooth out carefully. Combine the rest of the flour, sugar, brown sugar, and butter. Cut butter into dry mixture. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: broccoli soup
directions: *Enough to equal one pound, suggest 12 ounces Velveeta and 4 ounces jalapeno pepper.

title: oven baked caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Immediately pour over corn that has been placed in a large roasting pan.
Toss corn and syrup mixture to coat.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread coated corn onto waxed paper or cookie sheets and break up as it cools.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar with butter or lard.
Add molasses or dark Karo syrup and eggs.
Stir in spices sifted with flour.
Last, add the boiling water in which soda is dissolved.
Bake in well-greased loaf or muffin pans at 375° for 20 minutes and reduce heat to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
The batter will be very thin.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add rest of your ingredients.
Put in a shallow pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put in bean pot or 2-quart casserole dish.
Add
whole
onion in the center of the mixture.
Place strips of
bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: christmas punch
directions: Soften sherbet.
Mix a little juice into sherbet and then add all together.

title: the queen's pink martini
directions: Add all ingredients to shaker with lots of ice and shake, shake, shake!!! Pour into chilled martini glasses.

title: chicken-n-stuffing
directions: Cook chicken until done.
In a bowl put chopped chicken, soup, milk, egg and stuffing; mix well.
Melt butter; add to mixture. Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Stir in orange juice and rind.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir dry ingredients together; blend in.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned on edges.
Frost with icing.
Makes 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Boil raisins for 10 minutes in a small amount of water.
Drain and cool. Cream the brown sugar and butter.
Add oatmeal, soda and flour.
Put half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Next, mix egg yolks, sour cream, cornstarch and sugar.
Mix and boil, stirring constantly.
Add raisins and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over baked crust.
Crumble remaining oatmeal mixture over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spoon batter (tablespoon size) onto cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Remove from oven after 10 minutes at 350° and let cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and pat dry.
Tear spinach and lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Toss with sliced onion.
In jar with lid, combine other ingredients and shake well.
Before serving, toss dressing with salad.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour over cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: french tower torte
directions: Prepare 2 (9-inch) layer pans with butter and flour.
Peel and mash one banana to make 1/3 cup.
Drain pineapple well, reserving 1 cup juice for cake and pineapple for filling.
Follow package directions for cake using mashed banana and reserved pineapple juice instead of water.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.
Slice cooled cakes in half horizontally to make 4 layers.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, butter, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate dough until chilled.
Roll in balls; dip in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: toasted almond party dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Put into a 9-inch baking dish or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes.
Garnish with additional toasted almonds and keep warm. Serve with Melba toast and other breads.

title: "grown ups only" jigglers
directions: Mix vodka and Schnapps with boiling water.
Stir in gelatin. Dissolve completely.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; chill for at least 3 hours.
Cut into squares or cut with cookie cutters depending on holiday.

title: mulled tea and fruit punch
directions: It is suggested you make a paste of the ground cloves with a small amount of water (to prevent clouding).
Combine water, tea bags, sugar, cinnamon sticks and paste of cloves together.
Set aside to steep for several hours, then add fruit concentrates. Heat and serve.
Punch can be chilled, then reheated.

title: collard greens and ham hocks
directions: Cut and wash greens before starting.
Cut and wash pepper before starting.
Use large cook pot.
Place 1 1/2 quarts of water in pot.
Add seasoning salt, bring to boiling.
Add ham hocks and tenderizer.
Boil for 30 minutes, turn heat to medium.
Add collard greens and cook at this temperature for 30 more minutes.
Turn temperature to medium-low, add peppers.
Cover pot and let cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add more seasoning if needed. Best if served "hot."

title: low-fat punch bowl cake
directions: In your punch bowl, layer each of the following ingredients: angel food cake, strawberries, bananas, pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip. Continue to layer until all ingredients are gone, making sure that the Cool Whip ends up on top. Sprinkle with pecans (optional).
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Slice rolls in half crosswise. Spread mixture on both sides of rolls.
Place cheese and ham slices on bottom of rolls. Add top of rolls and slice rolls into individual servings.
Return to original pans.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 3 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: chinese ribs
directions: Heat grill.
Put ribs on grill over dripping pan.
Cook ribs until tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Meanwhile, in blender or food processor, puree garlic, ginger, soy sauce, wine and hoisin until smooth.
During last 30 minutes of cooking, baste ribs several times during cooking.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in seasonings.
Blend eggs and cheese. Stir into vegetable mixture. Spread rolls or pie crust in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish or 9-inch pie pan.
Spread mustard over crust.
Pour in vegetable mixture. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: chrissy's pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Stir until smooth.
Blend in walnuts.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal until fine powder; cream butter and both sugars. Add eggs and vanilla; mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add chips, candy and nuts. Roll into balls. Place on greased pan 2 inches apart. Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°. Do not overbake.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a large casserole dish.

title: championship chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in same bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla; stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups chips and nuts.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: popovers
directions: Stir together flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Add eggs and shortening.
Beat with a whisk for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot greased popover pans or earthenware cups and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve at once.
(I use large cupcake pans.)

title: chicken and rice
directions: Take a package of 6 to 12 hot dogs.
(Any brand will work equally well.)
Remove from cellophane wrapper, place in quart pan of water.
Bring to full boil; lower temperature and cover.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from burner.
Place hot dog on frankfurter roll and serve with relish of choice.
Makes 6 to 12 portions.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt, and yolks with a whisk in a large pot. Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Don't forget to stir.
Add cornstarch and stir until slightly thickened. It will not thicken like instant pudding until it cools.
You may have to add a little more cornstarch.
Add the vanilla.
Layer pudding, bananas, and wafers in a large rectangular dish.
Cover and put in the refrigerator overnight.

title: lentil stew
directions: Wash lentils thoroughly.
Put into pan with chopped carrots, onion, celery and garlic.
Cover with water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add browned sausage, tomatoes, parsley, vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pass the Parmesan cheese.

title: cashew shrimp
directions: * Available at Oriental markets.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Use long cookie sheet with sides.
Line with foil.
Place crackers on sheet; cover all spaces.
Bring to a boil the butter and sugar for 3 minutes, while stirring.
Pour over crackers. Spread over each.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Pour chips over and spread while hot.
Place in refrigerator for 15 minutes to set and cool.
Perforate squares; return to refrigerator to cool.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot, brown roast in oil.
Spoon off fat. Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cover; cook 45 minutes more until roast and vegetables are tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir flour and remaining 1/4 cup water into juices; bring to a boil and let thicken, stirring constantly. Pour over roast and serve.

title: skinny clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, boil water; add salt, potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Cook 20 minutes or until potatoes and celery are tender; add clams and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer five minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crusty cherry pudding
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice; add food coloring to juice. Combine 1/2 cup flour and 1 cup sugar in saucepan.
Add cherry liquid and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Add lemon juice and almond extract.
Cool.
Sift together 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and soda.
Add brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Press 1/2 oatmeal mixture into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Spread with cherry mixture; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven 30 minutes.
Serve while still warm.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Beat cream cheese in electric mixer until light and fluffy. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with an assortment of crackers, bread sticks or chips.
Combination of shrimp or other seafoods may be substituted for crab meat.

title: canned beef steaks
directions: Bring water, salt and sugar to a boil; cool.
Put steak slices in quart jars, fill with boiled juice.
Cold pack 3 hours.
Makes enough for 14 quarts.

title: rock cornish hens on rice mingle
directions: Day before serving:
Remove hens from freezer.
Place on large deep platter in refrigerator to thaw.
Early on the day to be served:
Remove giblets from hens, then wash and dry them. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, tie legs together with string.
Rub hens with soft butter, sprinkle with paprika; refrigerate.
Cook hens, uncovered, at 425° until well browned (about 1 hour), basting with melted butter.
Serve on Rice Mingle.
(Recipe for Rice Mingle can be found in the Vegetable Section.)

title: cheeseburger
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Pour meat into a crock-pot. Add taco sauce and Cheddar cheese soup; mix well.
Gradually add Velveeta while stirring.
Cook on low until cheese is completely melted.
Serve with your favorite chips.

title: creamy frozen lemon pudding
directions: Grease spring-form pan with butter.
Place tinfoil on cookie sheet under pan in case of dripping.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons crumbs on sides and bottom of pan.
Beat 6 egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Whip the cream in large bowl.
Fold in egg yolks then egg whites, then juice and rind.
Place 1/2 lemon mix in pan and cover with remaining crumbs.
Add rest of lemon mixture. Freeze, covered.
Allow 5 to 10 minutes to thaw.

title: eva st.  clair's holiday rice
directions: Place turkey necks and giblets in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add 2 quarts water.
Cook over low heat.
Add parsley, celery, carrots, onion and salt.
Cover; simmer 3 hours.
Remove celery, carrots, neck and giblets.
Save meat from neck.
Discard celery, carrots and giblets.
Return meat to pan.
Stir in butter, rice and mushrooms.
Simmer until rice is absorbed.

title: jambalaya
directions: Mix all except butter.
Put in 9x13-inch pan.
Pat butter on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1-1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: crunch oriental salad
directions: Pressing the packet plus 1/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup oil and 1/4 cup apple cider vinegar. Toss before serving. Add noodles last.

title: chicken magnifique
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Add mushrooms, soup, garlic, thyme and rosemary.
Cover and saute for 30 to 45 minutes until tender. Garnish with slivered almonds.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Grease or spray a square Pyrex or Corning Ware dish.
Heat in a saucepan the butter until melted.
Stir in sugar; set aside.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Spoon individual portions onto salad greens.
Serves 6.
Each serving contains approximately 220 calories.

title: dilled potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until they are still slightly firm but not too firm.
Cool potatoes, peel and cut into chunks as big as you desire.
Add all the remaining ingredients and toss with potatoes. Chill and serve.
Yield:
4 servings (1/2 cup each).

title: sesame crab cheese balls
directions: Drain crab and slice fine.
Blend softened cream cheese with lemon juice, mustard, Worcestershire, parsley and onion.
Mix until smooth.
Add drained pimiento and crab.
Mix well and chill. Shape into bite-size balls and roll in toasted sesame seed. Chill.
Serve on cocktail picks for appetizers.

title: nielson's favorite ice cream cake
directions: Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream, add powdered sugar, softened vanilla ice cream, pecans and chocolate chips.
Put 1-inch of mixture into the bottom of an angel food cake pan.
Alternate next with 3 types of sherbets, pushing them down to pack.
Finish with the remaining vanilla mix.
Freeze overnight.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix
first
4 ingredients well.
Pat out 3-ounce cakes. Dredge in
flour.
Fry in small amount of oil.
Brown on both sides, turning
only once.
Drain on paper towel and serve at once.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place meat in a roasting pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over the roast.
Spread cream of mushroom soup and water over top. Cover the pan and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: dallas lee's favorite dessert "blueberry delight"
directions: Combine flour, nuts, butter and salt.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar and spices, eggs and milk.
Pour into 13-inch by 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over batter.
Drizzle melted margarine over the cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 20.

title: farida's egyptian lentil soup
