directions: Fry onion in olive oil in large pot.
When onion is soft, add hot beef broth and lentils.
Simmer approximately 1/2 hour or until lentils are soft.
Strain soup through a mill and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add a pinch of cumin and a squeeze of lime and heat for a couple of minutes.
If consistency is too thick, add more water.
Serve with wedges of lime (the more lime the better) and buttered croutons.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: In large bowl mix 1/2 cup of the mushroom soup, beef, onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish firmly shape meat mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Spoon off 2 tablespoons drippings, reserve. In saucepan over medium heat, heat remaining soup, water and reserved drippings to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Thin sauce with additional water, if needed.
Spoon over meat loaf.

title: marge t.'s caesar salad
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Add to 2 heads of romaine lettuce.
Must be dry.
Add additional cheese to taste.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Place in a large saucepan. Add water.
Boil 2 minutes, then remove from heat and let soak 1 hour.
Boil soaked beans gently in sauce water for 45 minutes or until beans begin to soften. Drain beans, saving sauce water. Mix next 5 ingredients and catsup and add to beans in a baking dish.
Add enough sauce water to cover beans. Cook, covered, in a 250° oven for 5 hours. Crumble fried crisp bacon and add to beans; cook another 1 hour, uncovered.

title: sweet potato with pineapple
directions: Cook, peel and slice potatoes.
Cut pineapple into cubes and arrange in alternate layers with potato.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and flour; blend.
Add juice and cook.
Stir until it is thickened.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 20 minutes.
Serves 2.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: three bean bake
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp. Drain fat, but reserve 2 tablespoons to saute onion until soft.

title: easy blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine flour, sugar and egg; stir until mixture resembles coarse meal. Spread over berries. Drizzle butter over topping. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mama's pickled beets
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt and let come to a boil. Add beets; bring back to a boil. Simmer approximately 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 1 quart. Store in refrigerator.

title: tomato bowl
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Add tomatoes; let stand a few minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: no bake brownies
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in a heavy saucepan over medium heat until chips and marshmallows melt.
Cook and stir to a full all over boil and continue to boil 4 or 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in remaining ingredients.
Press mixture into a 9-inch buttered dish.
Chill 1 hour or until set.
Cut into 24 brownies.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all of the ingredients well.
Drop by tablespoonful onto hot greased grill or frying pan and cook until golden brown. Turn over and brown.
Serves six.

title: crab cakes
directions: In medium bowl, combine egg, 3/4 cup bread crumbs, mayonnaise, parsley, Worcestershire, seasoning and dry mustard.
Dispose of any shells in crabmeat.
Gently mix in crabmeat and form into cakes.
Coat crab cakes in remaining bread crumbs and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon margarine and 1 tablespoon oil.
Pan-fry for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: new braunsfels tortillas(flour)
directions: Mix dry ingredients, lard and finally hot water. Divide into 16 to 18 balls.
Roll out and cook on ungreased flat griddle, turning when browned.
Patches appear on bottom side. Brown second side and remove.
Store in Ziploc in refrigerator.

title: brown sugar icing
directions: Measure butter, milk and brown sugar into a heavy saucepan. Heat over low heat just enough for butter and sugar to melt.
Add salt and extract.
Mix well.
Add enough confectioners sugar to make right consistency to spread on layers (sometimes it takes a little more).

title: rich and delicious red velvet cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in cocoa and red food coloring.
Sift together flour and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Sprinkle soda over batter; pour vinegar and vanilla over batter and stir until well blended.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour sheet pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Bring to boil and add margarine, oil, cocoa and water.
Pour over sugar, flour, soda and salt while hot.
Mix together and add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into sheet cake pan and bake.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: *Fresh berries can be used when in season.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Let batter stand 5 minutes.
Carefully drop batter by level tablespoon into deep hot oil (370°).
Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: chocolate no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa on low heat.
Let come to a boil; add dash of salt while cooking.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Mix in well the peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let set.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Break eggs in bowl.
Put "big-big" handful of Crisco shortening into bowl.
Add sugar, flavoring of you choice and enough self-rising flour to make a stiff dough.
In palm of your hand, form marble size dough.
Shape round.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Cookies burn easily.
Remove from oven when tops are light brown.
Keeps crisp for weeks when stored in airtight container.

title: campfire sticky buns
directions: Rub one side of mess kit with butter.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Press into mess kit half that has butter on it.
Top with refrigerator biscuits.
Close mess kit and place in coals. Turn occasionally and check regularly to make sure it doesn't burn.

title: savory grilled potatoes
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and seasonings.
Stir in potatoes and onion; divide among 6 (12 inches each) heavy-duty foils.
Seal.
Grill over medium heat, covered, 25 to 30 minutes, until tender.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and salt together. Add milk.
Put oleo in bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Melt oleo in stove.
Pour batter over melted oleo; do not stir. Add the fresh fruit, thickened with corn syrup, on top of batter. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on top of fruit; do not stir.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup.
Add water and dissolve gelatin.
Pour in blender. Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend.
Chop remaining ingredients in a bowl and combine with soup mixture.
Pour in oiled square dish.

title: cal's cow tongue
directions: Cook cow tongue until fork goes in tongue easily.
Cook with salt and onion.
Cook and skin tongue.
Cut in slices.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix all of these ingredients and place in a glass or stainless bowl (don't use aluminum).
Cover with towel.
Allow to stand in warm place for a few days or until it has begun to ferment and has wonderful smell.
Cover and store in fridge; use as starter.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Combine into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until custard is done (about 1 hour).

title: delicious broccoli bake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together, uncooked, in a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Dot with 1/2 cup butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and garnish with onion rings.
Return to oven for an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: garlic-buttered shrimp
directions: Combine butter, onions and garlic in a 2-quart casserole dish; microwave on High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until onions are tender.
Add shrimp, lemon juice, salt and pepper, arranging the shrimp around outside of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 to 7 1/2 minutes, stirring twice and rearranging shrimp around outside of dish.
Stir in dill weed and parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute meat and drain.
Mix all the ingredients with meat in a casserole dish.
Cook covered for 1 hour.
Take off cover the last 15 minutes and let brown a little.

title: off-beat carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Place in 1-quart baking dish.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine horseradish and mayonnaise. (Taste, if horseradish is too strong, add more mayonnaise.)
Add onion and seasonings, mixing well.
Stir into carrots.
Saute bread crumbs in butter to coat.
Place on top of carrots.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cover cookie sheet with rolls and spread sausage onto rolls.
Then make one large jelly-like roll and slice up into individual rounds.
Place these flat on another cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until warm and lightly browned.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased 9-inch deep dish or 10-inch pie pan.
Place peaches over batter.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Add chili and mushroom soup.
Layer with chips and top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In an electric mixer, whip up all the ingredients.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water.
Let cool.
Set aside.
Cream brown sugar and white sugar with shortening.
Add eggs.
Add oatmeal.
Then add flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Bake in a 10 x 14-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Melt shortening; add beef, onion and pepper.
Brown slightly. Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Add macaroni, tomatoes, catsup, salt and pepper to browned mixture.
Mix and pour into a casserole.
To with cheese slices.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Spread all the following ingredients over butter and cracker crumbs.
Making layers, start with coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and then Eagle Brand milk. Spread nuts on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into small squares.
Makes 2 dozen or 1 pound.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add chili and cook until thoroughly heated.
Crush chips and make a layer in the bottom of a Pyrex dish.
Top with meat and chili mixture.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and green onions. Cover with foil for 15 minutes to allow cheese to melt.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: rice cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple that has been drained and rice.
Add pepper, onion, rice and seasoned salt.
Mix well and chill.
With wet hands form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans. Serve with celery and carrot sticks or party crackers.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: sparkling milk punch
directions: Combine milk and sherbet, beating with rotary mixer or electric mixer until frothy. Add ginger ale. Serve cold.
Serves 20.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Stir together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
If dough is sticky, add flour to handle.
Roll 1/4 thick on well floured board.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° for 8 minutes.

title: steak salad
directions: All ingredients to your own taste.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Combine fruits, marshmallows and coconut. Stir in sour cream and salt. Chill overnight.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with enough mayonnaise to make a smooth mixture.
Do not overmix.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Best if refrigerated overnight to let flavors mingle.

title: party spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill so flavors can blend.
Serve at room temperature as a spread for crackers.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Prepare chicken breasts in a pan of oil or use an inside grill. When chicken breasts are done, take them off and dice them. Place them in bottom of glass casserole dish. Crush Ritz crackers. In a shallow baking pan, place butter to melt. Mix butter with Ritz crackers and sprinkle poppy seeds in. Bake in oven until lightly toasted. Take out and set aside.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in the order given, beating well until each ingredients is added.
Use a well-greased pan.
(I use Baker's Joy.)
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 25 minutes.

title: homemade lollipops
directions: Brush inside surfaces of lollipop molds with oil; set aside.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cajun baked fish
directions: Combine mayonnaise and seasonings.
Brush fish with this mixture; coat with crumbs.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Fold in cheese.
Refrigerate.
If a creamier dressing is desired, whip in cheese with a mixer.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine flour, meal, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, oil and milk; beat well.
Grease 8 or 9-inch pan with bacon drippings. Grease pan well.
Heat pan in 450° oven until hot.
Pour batter in and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: company chicken pie
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add onion, salt and pepper.	Boil until tender (about 45 minutes).
Bone chicken and place pieces in bottom of buttered casserole dish.	Place eggs on top of chicken. Mix soup and broth pour over chicken and eggs.
Place rolls in a thin layer on top.	Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes, or until rolls are brown.
Serves 8.

title: chicken francese
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Dust chicken with flour. Dip in egg mixture (eggs, Romano cheese and Italian parsley) and saut in hot oil until light brown. Turn and cook other side. Remove to platter.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble.
Cook ground beef and onions until lightly browned.
Place bacon and beef mixture in a large casserole dish or crock-pot.
Add pork and beans, kidney beans and lima beans. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl. Stir into bean mixture.
Bake in regular oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Microwave 10 minutes on High.
Or cook in crock-pot 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli for 5 to 7 minutes and place in a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Melt in microwave cheese, margarine and milk.
Stir until creamy; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers on top and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
(Do not overcook.)

title: french canadian meat pie
directions: Combine pork, beef, onion and garlic in large heated skillet. Cook, stirring until meats lose pink color.
Stir in seasonings and water.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 10 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mashed potatoes.
Cool. Prepare pie crust.
Line 2 plates with bottom crusts.
Spoon half of meat into each pie shell.
Roll out top crusts; place over meat. Brush top with beaten egg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 25 minutes longer.

title: hot mulled cranberry cider
directions: Heat cranberry juice and apple juice in 3-quart saucepan, to boiling over high heat.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover and brew 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and ladle cider into mugs. Place cinnamon stick in each mug.
Serves 8.

title: pizza
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan, drain off fat.
Add oregano, garlic and half of the tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix flour and water to form paste.
Put half of dough in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Spread to edges.
Pour tomato sauce over it.
Add 4 slices of cheese, hamburger mixture, 4 slices of cheese, the rest of the dough and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Make enough basting mixture to keep the meat moist while cooking.
Alternative meats include a 12 to 14-pound shoulder or loin back ribs, cut in half.
Ask your butcher for recommendations. Sprinkle the dry barbecue seasoning on the meat 24 hours before cooking.
Steam the meat in a pan for 45 minutes.
Do not put the meat directly in the water.
Raise it above the waterline with a grill or some other device.
After the steaming process is complete, put all of the meat in a Webber Closed Cooker and let it cook for 12 to 14 hours.
Baste with vinegar-water periodically to keep it moist.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in chilies, chili powder, cumin, oregano and 1/2 cup salsa; set aside.

title: italian dressing
directions: Shake all
ingredients	in a tightly closed jar to mix. Shake before serving.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw 1 loaf of frozen bread dough.
Spread on greased cookie sheet like pizza.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together. Spread on dough like butter.
Cover with sliced pepperoni and Provolone cheese.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Place seam side down and close ends.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add egg and beat well.
Add applesauce and beat.
Add vanilla.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in 2 small or 1 large greased loaf pan at 325° about 1 hour.
Do not overcook.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in greased and floured muffin tins for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mixture may be kept in refrigerator for many days and use small amounts for breakfast each day.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350°.
In 15 minutes, reduce to 300° and bake for 45 to 50 minutes in greased and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not blend apples before adding to cake.

title: grandma's baked potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes or make 2 slits crosswise.
Rub with olive oil and bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove and wrap in foil.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
(The secret is in the olive oil.)

title: pear jello salad
directions: Cream the cheese and add 2 tablespoons pear juice; bring to boil 1 cup pear juice and add to lime Jell-O.
While still hot, blend in cream mixture.
Chill until syrupy (about 45 minutes); add whipping cream and drained crushed pears.
Chill overnight.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cucumbers and tomatoes.
Add the cucumbers and tomatoes before serving so the salad won't get watery.

title: lower fat chicken yorkshire
directions: Mix 1/4 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and dredge chicken breasts.
Brown in skillet sprayed with vegetable oil spray.
Remove chicken.
Save drippings for gravy.

title: creamy v-8 dressing
directions: In medium bowl, blend softened cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in mayonnaise until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Use as salad dressing or sandwich spread.
Reduced calorie cream cheese and mayonnaise can also be substituted.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter or oleo.
Add chili, corn and tomatoes; mix.
Pour in baking dish.
Prepare corn meal mix per directions on box.
Add cheese to mix.
Pour corn meal mix over the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy crab soup
directions: Cook meat 1 1/2 to 2 hours, then add vegetables and crab for 20 minutes.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of whipped cream.
Spread over crust.
Arrange strawberries in even layer. Using 3 1/2 cups cold milk, prepare pudding as directed on package. Pour over berries.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Shortly before serving, spread remaining whipped topping over pudding. Garnish with additional berries.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order given in a 12 x 9-inch glass dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Garnish with parsley before serving.

title: tuna puff
directions: In 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, combine soup, broccoli, tuna and nutmeg.
Lay slices of chestnuts over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat egg yolks until thick; add cheese. Beat egg whites until soft peak forms.
Fold in egg yolk mixture. Remove casserole from oven.
Spread mixture over top.
Bake 15 minutes or until browned.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Put juice in pan.
Heat until thawed.
Add tapioca or flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and bubbly.
Pour into pie crust.
Add top pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown for 35 minutes.

title: muddy brownies
directions: In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth and add vanilla.
Pour this mixture over cereal and stir until cereal is evenly coated.
In a Ziploc bag or large plastic bowl with cover, add coated cereal to powdered sugar and stir until each piece is evenly coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: kielbasa cabbage pot
directions: In Dutch oven heat sliced kielbasa over low heat, about 10 minutes, to draw out fat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add cabbage and water.
Cover and cook 9 minutes until cabbage is barely tender.
Core and chop 3 apples.
Add apples and carrots. Mix sugar, vinegar and seasonings and pour over.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
The last 5 minutes, core and cut into wedges the last apple.
Heat in butter until barely soft.
Serve with apple wedges on top of kielbasa/cabbage mixture.
Serves 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine and mix with pastry blender or hands.
Form into balls, about golf ball size, and bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together well.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda and vanilla mixture.
Stir in gradually flour and salt sifted together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll out onto lightly floured board to 1/3-inch thickness.
Bake until light brown at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown all ingredients and drain.
Add beans, ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix.
Pour into casserole dish and bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot milk cake with coconut frosting
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Heat milk and butter to boil and remove from heat.
Add milk to first mixture. Do not use a beater. Mix well by hand.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in an 8-inch square greased pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
You may not want the whole bottle of salad dressing.
Start with half the bottle.
Experiment!

title: jello gelatin(i'm not squares)
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter. Press mixture into bottom
of
x
9-inch
pan.
Chill
15 minutes. Beat cream cheese and sugar, gradually beat in milk. Then fold in Cool
Whip.
Spread
mixture
evenly
over
crumb crust topped with
peaches.
Dissolve
jello in boiling water, combine cold water and ice to
make
1/4 cups, add to jello and spoon over peaches.
Chill
at
least 3 hours before serving.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use a Good Seasons Italian dressing using lemon juice instead of vinegar or any dressing you might prefer.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil margarine, brown sugar and nuts for 3 minutes.
Cover cookie sheet with tin foil.
Break graham crackers into pieces (half). Cover the top of each cookie with some of the caramelized
mixture. Place cookies in 300° oven and bake for 9 minutes.

title: cabbage in a skillet
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet and cook about 20 minutes over medium heat.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix together and pour in odd shapes into hot grease in a skillet.
Brown and sprinkle with powdered sugar on top after cooking.

title: steak cubes hawaiian
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Heat oil in heavy skillet. Add garlic and meat; brown well.
Drain oil from pan.
Add syrup from pineapple, salt, pepper, ginger, chicken consomme and half of vinegar.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Add celery, green pepper and onions.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add tomato wedges and pineapple chunks.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Drain pineapple juice and mix with pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add chunk pineapple and mix well.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and chocolate.
Melt margarine and add to eggs.
Beat well and pour in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Pie can be made with or without crust.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes in an 8-inch pie pan.
Serve warm with ice cream on top.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: In large end of each crescent roll, put a hunk of chicken and cheese.
Roll it up.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: cereal candy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt almond bark.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Makes a lot.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill. Line two plates with lettuce.
Spoon half of tuna salad onto each plate.
(May use low-fat yogurt in place of mayonnaise.)
Yield: 2 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts and spread butter or margarine to taste, then place bread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage to crumble, drain well, then spoon over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and salt, then pour over cheese. Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients together; add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
I do not get my mixer out; I stir until it is smooth and creamy.
Bake 30 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: magic giant bubbles
directions: Gently mix, trying to avoid making bubbles on the surface. The less bubbles on the surface of the mixture, the stronger the bubbles will be.
Different sized circular objects (even 6-pack plastic rings) make for great bubble fun!

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in the cup of warm water.
Add sugar, salt and melted shortening.
Pour into pan, add flour 1/2 cup at a time. Knead dough until it is soft and smooth.
Place in greased pan. Place in warm area for 1 hour.
Brush top of dough with soft shortening before it rises.
After rising, divide in 1/2 and roll out on floured table.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix gelatin with 2 cups boiling water. Add frozen strawberries, juice and all. Let thicken in refrigerator until thick enough to add one large Cool Whip. Fold in well. Pour over angel food cake which has been broken into small pieces in a large bowl. Mix well. Pour into large angel food cake pan (or pans); push down a little with a spatula. Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: fresh strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon in large bowl and put hole in middle.
In small bowl, mix oil, eggs and strawberries.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup and uncooked rice.
Mix together; cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Mix together and let stand for 10 minutes.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten cookie when put on sheet.
Decorate with colored sugar, nuts, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix all ingredients except cereal.
In microwave or double boiler, put cereal in large bowl and pour chocolate mixture over it.
Stir until well coated.
Place 1 pound powdered sugar in large paper bag.
Put coated cereal in bag and shake until well coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: four layer party dessert
directions: Melt oleo and combine with flour and 3/4 cup pecans.
Mix until crumbly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cool at least 2 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix well and form balls.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.
Can take out chopped celery and use mixture on celery sticks.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In blender or food processor, chop dried beef.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Blend well.

title: summer fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a shallow baking dish with 2 tablespoons of the butter and arrange the fruit in the base.
In bowl of a food processor, briefly combine the remaining butter with the flour and sugar until the mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over fruit.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until top becomes crisp and fruit collapses.
Serve warm with the sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in pan and coat pan.
Mix Corn-Kits, Bis-Kits and baking powder.
Add milk, margarine and eggs to make thick-pouring mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peach pandowdy
directions: Pour peaches into a 2-quart basin.
Make a batter with the milk, egg, melted butter and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make thick enough to roll out.
Cover the peaches.
Put paper over.
Bake until the crust is done.
Eat with vanilla sauce (see sauce section).

title: barley soup
directions: Let boil about 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven 350°.

Combine 1 cup sugar, and shortening. mix well. Add beaten eggs, and apples. Mix in dry ingredients, vanilla and buttermilk. Add pecans. Mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan. Sprinkle top with remaining sugar and cinnamon. Bake for 1 hour. Can test with toothpick.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt in extra-large bowl; make a well in the center of mixture. Combine egg substitute, yogurt and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moist. Spoon mixture into muffin pans coated with cooking spray, filling 3/4 full. Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Remove muffins from pan immediately. Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: greek salad
directions: Place tomatoes, cucumber, onion and peppers in large salad bowl.
Shake in a jar until well blended the olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over salad.
Sprinkle Feta cheese, olives and parsley over the top.
(Can be made ahead.)
Serves 4.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello until jello is dissolved; cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill until firm.
May sprinkle coconut on top.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine
butter,
sugar,
cocoa and milk and bring to a boil, stirring
constantly.
Boil
1 minute; remove from heat and
add the
peanut butter, stirring until it's well melted. Pour
over the oatmeal and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons onto sheets of waxed paper.
Cool until set.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Boil fruit in 1 cup water.
Add margarine.
Let cool.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cream the butter, oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add chocolate and mix well.
Sift flour and sugar.
Add alternately with sour milk to chocolate mixture; beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in three 9-inch round pans, greased and floured.

title: easy cheese potato
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese; mix well.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chicken morango
directions: Mix wine, soup	and sour cream together.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer
by
ingredient, starting with noodles and pouring soup mixture over top, then top with Parmesan.
Or you can mix all
together and top with Parmesan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In large pot, combine all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Simmer one hour.
Place broken chips in bottom of serving bowls.
Add soup and top with cheese.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer all vegetables.
Mix together Miracle Whip, sour cream, bacon drippings and sugar with about 1/4 cup milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Crumble bacon and place cheese and bacon on top. Cover and refrigerate. Better to let marinate overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dice chicken into a mixing bowl and add onion, garlic salt, chili powder and tomatoes.
Reserve 1 cup of cheese for topping. Add remaining cheese to chicken mixture.
Soften tortillas in chicken broth; line a large baking dish.
Add chicken mixture and about 1/2 cup of broth.
Spread both cans of soup on top. Sprinkle reserved cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil hard for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon soda; pour over popped corn.
Stir well.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 to 3 times.
Will stay crisp for weeks in tight container.

title: texas chili
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, onion, green pepper and garlic. Drain fat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: baked pheasant with sauce
directions: Mix dressing, soup mix and jam.
Pour over pheasant pieces. Let marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tender.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix together buttermilk and eggs.
Stir together first 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Add milk and eggs mixture, stirring until just moistened.
Heat oil in baking pan.
Pour into cornbread mixture and stir.
Pour back into baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Excellent for dressing!

title: seven stars cucumber salad
directions: Grate cucumbers (or slice thinly), salt and cover with ice water.
Place covered in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Drain well. Add vinegar, tarragon, pepper and sour cream to cucumbers and toss well.
Serve with fish.

title: chili
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients and bring to boil; turn down to simmer for 1 hour.
Add chili powder and ketchup.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Add onion.
Let cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cherry pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Make 1/4-inch slices of butter and arrange them over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix crumbs with melted margarine and line a 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice bananas onto crumb crust.
Mix Eagle Brand with lemon juice, pour on top of bananas.
Spoon pineapple over for next layer. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut on Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups milk.
Add butter in a saucepan until scalded. Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Make a paste with remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Add to scalded milk mixture and cook until slightly thickened.
Stirring constantly, add beaten eggs, cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cook squash and onions until tender.
Melt butter and stir in Stove Top stuffing.
Line dish with half of the crumbs and save rest for top.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken kisses
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone.
Chop your chicken up in small pieces.
Mix cream cheese and chopped onions together.
Roll out rolls into a triangle.
Put a spoonful of chicken and a spoonful of your cream cheese mix on the top of your chicken.
Bring the edges of your rolls up and pinch at the top.
Brush melted butter over top of rolls and put them on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: orange muffins(kentucky style)
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs.
Beat in orange juice and grated rind of orange.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda into mixture.
(Batter should not be too stiff.)
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
This makes 24 muffins.
Crushed fresh strawberries or blueberries may be substituted for orange juice and rind.
Muffins may be iced, if desired.

title: micro chicken livers
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat in microwave oven on Full power for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Coat liver in flour.
Arrange in melted butter.
Cook in microwave oven on Full power for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes or until livers are no longer pink.

title: slow cooker black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas overnight in water; drain.
Combine in slow cooker with other ingredients.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Mix and bake in preheated Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dip for mushrooms
directions: Fry mushrooms in cooking oil, then dip mushrooms in dip.

title: peach and fruit cocktail cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
When hot, add flour and sugar; then add peaches, fruit cocktail and water.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 paper or plastic cups (7 ounce).

title: hot cider punch
directions: In 32 cup electric coffee maker, pour apple cider.
In the strainer part, put rest of ingredients.
Let cider perk through ingredients.
Smells and tastes delicious.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets; dice; chop eggs.
Fry onion and bacon together; reserve bacon grease.
Add onion and bacon to potato mixture.
Add bacon grease (as much as you want) slowly to beaten egg; beat well.
Add vinegar and salt.
Pour over potato mixture; mix well.
Heat in a double boiler.
Serve hot.
Serves about 6.

title: lace cookies
directions: Butter 2 baking sheets.
Melt remaining butter.
Flour pans lightly and shake off excess flour.
Stir together the remaining ingredients except milk.
Continue stirring until the sugar is melted, then stir in the milk.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Cook in oven.

title: busy day fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients and add milk.
Pour milk mixture into margarine.
Do not stir.
Add fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious with ice cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and oleo together.
Add beaten eggs and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix well and pour half in bottom of greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon. Sprinkle half of this on cake in pan. Put remaining cake mix and top with sugar mixture. Take a knife and run through batter to swirl. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan crisp
directions: Finely chop 1/2 cup pecans; reserve rest of pecan halves for garnish.
In large bowl, measure pecans and remaining ingredients. Knead until mixture holds together.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of food processor or blender and process, turning on and off until sauce is formed with small bits of basil still visible.

title: fruit of the spirit pie
directions: Mix cheese, milk, pineapple and lemon juice.
Put in crusts. Slice 2 bananas on each pie.
Mix other ingredients and spread on pie.
Chill.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cut in Crisco. Mixture will be crumbly.
Combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add to mixture, stirring only until combined.
Add chips and nuts.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add soda to tomato soup.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add nuts (walnuts better).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Frost with buttercream frosting.
Top with walnuts.

title: homemade tootsie rolls
directions: Melt chocolate.
Put all the ingredients in a heavy-duty freezer Ziploc bag.
Zip it closed securely, eliminating as much air as possible.
Place bag in another bag.
Eliminate the air and securely zip the closure.
Squeeze the contents until they are thoroughly mixed. Roll the Tootsie Rolls into small logs and place on waxed paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Blend in sugar, salt and egg.
Melt butter and stir in bananas.
Dissolve soda in water and add flour. Mix and put in loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy strawberry fruit salad
directions: Mix jello with pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit in medium bowl.
Sprinkle with Sweet 'N Low.
Stir thoroughly.
Chill.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash avocados; add remaining ingredients.
Mix with French dressing or lemon juice.
Serve on lettuce leaves or crackers as hors d'oeuvres.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Add 1 tablespoon melted butter and the milk.
Stir until well blended. Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Cream butter; add Sucaryl, vanilla and egg, blending well.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Stir in the chocolate pieces.
Drop onto a slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together.
Put in pan.
Place in oven.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown, stirring occasionally.
When cool, put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy chicken
directions: Combine dressing, cranberries and onion soup mix; blend and pour over chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
(Boned chicken can be used; baking time will be less.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add egg yolks.
Add a little warm milk, a little at a time, to the mixture.
Add vanilla.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly until thick. After custard cools, arrange banana and vanilla wafers in 2-quart Pyrex container, alternating layers.

title: aunt maude's anise cookies(just for fun)
directions: By hand, beat eggs one hour.
Mix sugar, flour, hortshorn, anise and butter together.
Stir in beaten eggs slowly.
Roll out and press with cookie forms marked on rolling pin.
Cut out and let stand overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 24 dozen.

title: egg and honey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Stir in honey, oil, eggs and 3 3/4 cups flour.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead dough about 5 minutes, adding flour until smooth and elastic.
Coat large bowl with oil.
Place dough in bowl, turning to coat with oil on all sides.
Cover; let rise until doubled.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet.
Add garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Add chicken and brown.
Stir in asparagus.
Cook 3 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, thyme and wine.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Heat Alfredo sauce and pour over hot pasta.
Serve pasta on plates; spoon chicken mixture over pasta.
Serve with crusty French bread and a salad.

title: fancy meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat balls. Remove from skillet and drain fat.
Place chili sauce and cranberry sauce in skillet.
Stir constantly until cranberry sauce is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: corn and crab quesidilla creations
directions: Fill bowl with cheese.
Mix all ingredients except oil and tortillas.
Place oil in a frying pan.
Lay a tortilla in your pan and stuff the tortilla with ingredients.
Place another tortilla on top; hold together with a toothpick.
Fry until melted.
Great appetizers.

title: white chili
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion, garlic and cumin until onion is tender.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine onion mixture with kidney beans, garbanzo beans, corn, chiles, bouillon and 1 1/2 cups water. Cover casserole and bake 50 to 60 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together butter, sugar, milk and flavoring until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crab mold
directions: Bring undiluted soup to a boil.
Add cream cheese.
When melted, add mayonnaise and stir.
Mix gelatin and water together and add to soup.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into mold. Refrigerate.

title: cheese barbecue
directions: Combine cheese, eggs, catsup, onion, green pepper, olives, butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on bottom half of each bun.
Broil bottom halves in broiler for 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Place top halves of buns under broiler until lightly toasted.
Serve immediately.

title: okra hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil until just moistened.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep, hot oil. Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Pour tomatoes in a large soup pot, crushing tomatoes with your fingers.
Bring to a boil.
Add olive oil and red pepper.
Rinse shrimp and peel shell off each shrimp and add to tomatoes.
Stir occasionally.
Cut cabbage into 1-inch pieces and add to soup. Simmer on medium heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally or until cabbage is tender.
Salt to taste.
Serve with crusty Italian bread and butter.

title: mama clubb's quick enchiladas
directions: Brown turkey in a saucepan and drain.
Mix the taco seasonings in 1 1/4 cups water until lumps are gone.
Add to turkey.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until the water is mostly gone or thickened.
Add corn, drained.
Simmer a minute or two longer.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Will need another smaller dish for remaining enchiladas.
Spoon meat mixture into the tortillas.
Put into baking dishes.
Pour enchilada sauce over the middle of the tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese over the tortillas.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts and the sauce begins to thicken and the ends of the tortillas get firm to almost crispy.

title: salsa
directions: Blend chopped green onions, spices and jalapenos with tomato sauce.
Blend until chopped well.
Add whole tomatoes and mix until blended, but still chunky.
Serve with chips.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Chop all vegetables.
Mix pasta and vegetables.
Add Italian dressing, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: spanish baked fish(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Dampen fish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and mace.
Oil a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Arrange onion slices over bottom.
Add pimiento.
Top with fish slices, arranged side by side.
Add green onion.
Add mushrooms over the top.
Add wine.
Brown the crumbs in the butter.
Sprinkle over the top of the fish.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes in moderate oven, 350°.
Serve with Spanish rice.

title: chicken casserole with no chicken
directions: Put 1 cup of the dressing in bottom of 11 x 4-inch glass baking dish.
Combine milk, sour cream, soup, onion flakes and margarine. Add drained veggies to mix.
Pour over layer of Stove Top dressing. Add rest of Stove Top and smooth.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: annie's breaded chicken legs
directions: Brush on mayonnaise.
Rub in crumbs.
Line pan with foil. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and pudding. Beat in eggs. Add flour and soda, then oats. Raisins are optional. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crazy cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and drop so it will fall.
Bake until done.

title: cheese pie roll
directions: Overlap 2 sheets of wax paper.
Let Velveeta cheese.
Set to room temperature.
Knead cheese like dough to get soft.
Roll out into a circle on waxed paper.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Add onions and peppers (6 to 8) and mix thoroughly. Pour mixture on half of circle; spread and flip over like an omelet.
Take a spoon dipped in soft butter and mash edges together like a fried pie.
Do the decorative edge after you flip onto a serving dish.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix margarine, eggs, sweetener, vanilla flavoring and cinnamon until creamy.
Add flour.
Fold in dates, bananas and applesauce. Mix well. Bake in a loaf pan at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: arva's divinity
directions: You also need a deep saucepan.
Don't make on a rainy day or when a lot of moisture is in the air.
It won't set up.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix together and roll out to 1/4 to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut and sprinkle
with	garlic	powder	over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20
minutes.
Turn
off
oven
and
let them dry overnight right
in
the
oven.
Store
in airtight container. Your dog will love them.

title: arkansas chicken and rice
directions: Spread 2-quart casserole with baking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute green pepper and onion.
Place in large bowl; add cooked chicken, cooked rice, green beans, mayonnaise, celery soup, chestnuts, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Stir well and pour into prepared casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes, until melted.

title: butterhorn rolls(always brings praise)
directions: Combine corn, cornmeal, half the Cheddar cheese, the milk, eggs, peppers, salt and baking soda in bowl.
Mix well.
Put butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole (preferably a glazed Mexican earthenware casserole) or 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Place in preheated hot oven (400°) until butter is hot but not until brown.
Immediately pour in the batter.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
If after about 35 minutes, the top appears too brown.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix ingredients, adding egg whites last.
Place in three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: tangy party dogs
directions: Heat all ingredients, except hot dogs, in saucepan on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
When it comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces and put in crock-pot. Pour sauce over hot dogs in crock-pot and turn on low.

title: sesame whole wheat braided bread(from "a diary of bread")
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, ginger and salt in a large bowl.
Mix 1 tablespoon of the beaten egg with 1 tablespoon water in a small bowl.
Set aside to be used later for glaze.
Add the remaining eggs, 2 1/4 cups warm water and oil to flour mixture. Beat in 4 cups of all-purpose flour and 1 cup whole wheat flour.

title: delicate pineapple cake
directions: Mix pudding and cream cheese.
Place in refrigerator.
In two 9-inch pans, bake layers as directed on cake mix.
Cool completely.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meats and drain well. Put meats and all other ingredients in crock-pot and heat slowly to melt cheese and blend flavors.
Serve with chips.

title: pork chop dish
directions: Cook pork chops
until
brown.
Place
in deep dish with potatoes on top.
Put
mushrooms
on this.
Add a little water; cook in 350° oven until potatoes are done.

title: strawberry quick bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients. Stir just to mix and moisten.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until knife comes out clean.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spinach mold
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in hot water.
Add vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Cook, drain and cool chopped spinach.
When jello has cooled, beat until fluffy.
Add cottage cheese, onion, celery and spinach.
Crushed bacon may be added. Mix together and pour into mold.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Clean (do not peel) and chop zucchini fine.
Chop cheese and onion fine.
Mix together; add bread crumbs and salt.
Beat 2 eggs and add to mixture.
Place 1 teaspoon oil in muffin tin; add 1 tablespoon mixture in each tin.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown and crusty in 375° oven.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen appetizers.

title: potato enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas by dipping in hot oil (do not cook long, they will be tough).
Fry potatoes to soft stage.
Fry ground meat with onions.
Melt cheese with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Roll mixture of meat and potatoes in each tortilla.
Place in a large baking pan or dish.
Cover with melted cheese and Ro-Tel mixture.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: herb chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then sprinkle over chicken. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: rice cake candy bar
directions: Spread peanut butter on rice cake.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup on top.
Sprinkle with raisins or bananas.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Enjoy.

title: folsum cole slaw(from a little cafe in des moines, new mexico.)
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a full boil, stirring frequently. In a large bowl, layer cabbage and onions alternately, using 1/2 to 3/4-cup salad oil as you layer. Pour over HOT salad dressing; cover and let stand for an hour. Slightly fork-stir, cover tightly and refrigerate for several hours (24 is better).
Fork-stir before serving.

title: barbecued chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together (can make hot).
Pour over meat and cook in dish or pan covered at 325° to 350°.
Keep meat covered with sauce while it bakes.
Can be made night before, left in sauce, then baked.

title: frosted angel torte
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package.
Pour milk into refrigerator trays; place in freezer and chill until partially frozen, about 1 hour.
Split cake to make 3 layers.
Sprinkle gelatin on water to soften; place over boiling water to dissolve. In chilled bowl, beat milk and sugar with chilled beaters on high speed until fluffy.
Beat in lemon peel, lemon juice, food color and dissolved gelatin until very stiff.
Fill cake layers, spreading each with about 1/3 of filling.
Frost top with remaining filling.
Freeze cake.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
Because of the filling, refrigerate leftover cake.
Makes 16 servings, at 140 calories each.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and sugar together.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each of them.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Pour the mixture into a greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: secret crawfish dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream together until smooth.
Add garlic, salt pepper and crawfish or shrimp.
Needs to be refrigerated 2 hours before serving.

title: herbed french bread
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch slices. In a small bowl, combine the butter, parsley and chives. Spread over one side of each slice of bread. Place buttered side up on an ungreased baking sheet. Broil 4-inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 10 servings.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown well in their own fat in a skillet.
Turn down heat; add water and simmer 45 minutes, turning once (adding more water if needed).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Turn into greased shallow pan.
Pat mixture into loaf shape.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn out onto hot platter; garnish with parsley.
Place in well-greased muffin tin for individual loaves.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Yield:
6 servings.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shake well before pouring over dry slaw mix.
Makes 2 gallons (enough for 400 servings).

title: copper pennies
directions: Bring sliced carrots to boil.
Drain.
Cut pepper and onion in slices on strips.
Take remainder of ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps for weeks.
Good with all meats.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix well; make into patties.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: sue anne's fruit pizza
directions: Mix with mixer on low speed until butter is fine or cut with pastry cutter.
Press onto pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marinated brisket of beef
directions: Season beef with salt, pepper, garlic powder and seasoned salt.
Place in a shallow dish, cover with dressing and marinate several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: pineapple angel dessert
directions: In a small bowl, gradually blend milk into cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Add pudding mix and beat at low speed until slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.
Pour pudding mixture over angel cake cubes, stirring to coat.
Turn into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread drained pineapple over top.
Spread dessert topping or cream over all.
Chill for a few hours or overnight.

title: rheinlscher sauerbraten
directions: Beef should be well larded with thin strips of bacon.
Tie meat with string in several places so it can be turned.
Rub meat with salt and place in deep close fitting glass or earthenware dish.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bar and spread on top.
Cut into squares when set.

title: grandma's stuffing
directions: Saute onion. Boil eggs and peel. Cut up and set aside. Heat soup; add eggs and crumble all crackers. Add onions. Mix all ingredients together. Let set for 10 minutes. Ready to eat.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: In frying pan, brown hamburg and drain.
Add celery, onion, mushrooms and green pepper; bring to a boil.
Cook for about 15 minutes or until celery, onion, mushrooms and pepper are done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Remove crust from bread and butter.
Place in bottom of dish.
Brown sausage; drain and sprinkle over bread.
Grate cheese and put over sausage.
Beat eggs and half and half together.
Pour over sausage and cheese. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix well and keep in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely, can be added to.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken and remove fat, bones and skin.
Stir dressing and other ingredients together.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan, put layer of dressing, a layer of chicken, then a can of soup and broth mixed. Repeat again and top with other can of soup and broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: In a bowl, mix together smashed cookies and melted butter. Mix together.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture for top of cake.
Press remaining cookie mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread softened ice cream over the cookie crust.
Cover ice cream with Hershey's topping. Spoon Cool Whip over and sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve. Cut into squares.

title: maggie's chicken sandwich
directions: Cook chicken; cut into small pieces.
Mix chicken, celery, almonds, grated cheese, grated onion, lemon juice, Accent salt and pepper together with the mayonnaise.
Spread on rolls.
Wrap each roll in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: white onion soup
directions: Peel onions and slice thinly.
In a large saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Add onions and saute, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes, until they are soft.
Add wine.
Cook, stirring gently, until liquid has almost evaporated.
Add water. Bring to a boil.
Add oregano and thyme.
Simmer over low heat, uncovered, for about 45 minutes.

title: mrs. isaac's chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries well; let stand on paper toweling.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender and drain. Beat eggs and stir in mayonnaise and add rest of ingredients.

title: cracker barrel lemon pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Add lemon juice.
Pour in crust.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 8 minutes; cool.
Top with whipped topping.

title: bread and butter microwave pickles
directions: Layer sliced cucumbers and onion in microwave dish.
Mix salt, spices, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave on High for 7 minutes. Stir and let cool or can keep in refrigerator in sterilized jars.

title: dixie's chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice as directed on box.
Boil chicken with salt, celery (2 stalks) and onion or onion salt.
When cooked and deboned, cut into bite size chunks.
Saute celery and onions in 1/2 stick butter.
Mix first 4 ingredients together with 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add other ingredients except eggs.
Beat until mixed, then add eggs.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, syrup, nuts and water in 2-quart microproof bowl. Cook on High for 5 minutes; stir.
Cook on High for 13 1/2 minutes (until it separates into threads).
Stir in the butter, soda and vanilla until bubbly.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Add the onion, some parsley, celery, rosemary, bay leaf, cloves, tomato, salt, pepper, sugar, mushrooms and liquor and wine to the hen; stew very slowly until tender.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all together.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Form into two balls.
Roll in 1 cup chopped walnuts and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: gail's strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Pour over strawberries and chill in refrigerator for at least an hour before serving.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Leeks have a great deal of sand between the leaves and must be carefully cleaned.
Trim off root end and cut off and discard the long green stems.
Split leeks lengthwise from the stem end, then turn and split them one more time.
Rinse well.
Separate leaves under cold running water, then chop into 1/4-inch pieces.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch cubes (about 2 c.).
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a saucepan; add onions and chopped leeks. Cook over medium heat, stirring until wilted.
Do not brown. Add potatoes, chicken broth, water, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat. Remove bay leaf, add remaining butter and stir.
Adjust seasonings and serve piping hot with croutons.

title: toffee tassies
directions: For pastry, in a mixing bowl beat the 1/2 c. margarine or butter and the cream cheese until teaspoon of pastry evenly into the bottom and up sides of 24 ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin cups. Set aside.
For filling, beat together brown sugar, egg and 1 Tbsp. melted margarine or butter.
Stir in the chopped pecans. Spoon 1 tsp. of filling into each pastry-lined cup. Sprinkle about 1 tsp. Heath bits on each.
Bake in a 325° oven about 30 minutes or until pastry is golden and filling is puffed.
Cool slightly in pans on wire racks.
Remove and cool completely on white racks. Makes 24 tassies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken quarters until tender.
Remove meat from bone. Cut fine and mix with rest of ingredients.
Mix flour, oleo and milk and pour over chicken mixture in shallow pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, then 15 minutes at 450°.

title: grandma pratt's casserole
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread mushroom soup over hamburg.
Sprinkle drained green beans on next, then cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: curly pasta salad
directions: Mix together the first 11 salad ingredients.
Put lemon juice, vinegar, garlic, Parmesan, salt, pepper, basil, oregano and olive oil in blender and blend well.
Pour dressing over first mixture and combine well.
The salad should be made at least 6 to 8 hours before serving so flavors can blend.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Soak whole cucumbers in ice water 1/2 day.
Place in bottom of each quart jar:
alum, hot pepper, dill and garlic buttons.
Split cucumbers lengthwise and packed loosely in jars.
Heat vinegar, 3 quarts water and canning salt.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal each jar as it is filled.

title: caramel bars
directions: Unwrap caramels and put in pan with milk, then set aside.
Mix flour, oatmeal, sugar, soda, salt and butter.
Put 3/4 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pepper.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Sift black pepper lightly on top.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes in 400° preheated oven.
Best if removed from oven 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: yogurt apple salad
directions: Peel, core and cube apples.
In mixing bowl, add together apple cubes, raisins, walnut pieces, chopped celery and orange yogurt.
Let flavors blend in refrigerator. Serve within 1 hour of adding yogurt.

title: navajo tacos
directions: Mix ingredients and let set for 15 minutes. Pat into tortilla sizes. Fry in hot oil until light brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix and cover chicken.
Bake covered 2 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Mix and spread onto bread the cream cheese, Miracle Whip, Worcestershire sauce, onion powder and shredded cheese.
Layer onto bread the ham, turkey, tomato and lettuce leaves (if desired).
Put halves of bread together and cut into 2-inch slices.

title: nachos
directions: Spread tortilla chips in a single layer on ovenproof plate or foil lined baking sheet. Cut cheese into 3/4 x 3/4 x 1/4-inch pieces. Cut peppers into thin strips about 3/4-inch long.
Place a piece of cheese on each chip. Top with a strip of chilli. Bake in a 400° oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: easy chocolate drops
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg, cocoa mixture and sour milk with soda.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add flour last, then nuts. Drop on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing while hot.
Not a good keeper.
Best eaten soon.
Make sour milk by adding vinegar to sweet milk.

title: wild rice seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Use a large casserole dish; may be frozen.

title: chocolate raisins
directions: Combine chocolate chips and syrup in top of a double boiler. Stir over boiling water until melted.
Add confectioners sugar, orange flavoring and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Chill.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Make a well in the center; stir in undrained raspberries and beaten eggs.
Thoroughly mix in oil and pecans. Spoon batter into paper liners in muffin pan.
Muffin cups will be full.
Batter is heavy and will not overflow.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before taking from pan.
Makes 12.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine in separate bowl rest of ingredients, then cover chicken with sauce.
Bake 2 hours at 350° or until chicken is done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels and margarine; spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Drain fruit in colander and save juice.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until blended; add Cool Whip and mix.
Spread over pretzels and refrigerate.
Boil 2 cups juice and dissolve jello; cool.
(If you don't have 2 cups of juice, add a little water.)
Put fruit in jello and pour over the top.
Refrigerate.

title: creole steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika, pepper and then dredge meat in mixture.
Save flour that remains.
Brown onions and green peppers in shortening in skillet.
Remove them and brown meat in remaining shortening.
Cover meat with onions; sprinkle rice over this and top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle remaining flour over this and cover tightly.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix with just one egg and enough water to make mixture stiff.

Spray an 8x10 glass dish with butter cooking spray. Put cake mix in dish and pat out flat. Mix potatoes, nutmeg, vanilla, sugar and one egg. Pour over cake mix. Bake for about 1 hour in a 325 degree oven.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage that has been shredded in greased baking dish. Brown hamburger with onion.
Stir in rice.
Place meat and rice mixture on cabbage.
Mix soup with water and pour over ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: sugar pie(torte au sucre)
directions: Line pan with pastry.
Reserve enough for lattice top.
Fill pie shell with sugar.
Do not pack.
Moisten with cream and dot with butter.
Cover with lattice pastry.
Bake in a preheated oven for 10 minutes at 425°, then lower heat to 375° and bake 25 minutes longer.
Serve with unsweetened whipped cream.
When pie is served warm, the filling will be slightly runny.
If refrigerated the filling will be firm.

title: green bean oriental
directions: Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid. Brown almonds in oil. Add celery and saute 2 minutes. Add bean liquid, chicken stock, soy sauce, sugar and the vinegar.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes. Stir in the beans and heat.
Add cornstarch mix and heat until thickens.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: Make stuffing as on box directions; set aside.
In a large bowl, blend soup, turkey, celery and onions together until creamy. Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan or casserole dish, then put 1/2 stuffing in pan.
Pour soup mixture over stuffing and spread evenly across.
Crumble remaining stuffing across entire pan; spread cheese over the top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: harvest moon lemon dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix well with electric mixer the cheese and sugar.
Add 9 ounce carton Cool Whip last.
Spread over cooled crust.
Spread cooled boxed pudding over mixture.
Then spread one 4 1/2 ounce carton Cool Whip over top of pudding.
Chill several hours.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend all ingredients thoroughly. Spoon batter into greased muffin tins until half full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in vegetable oil at medium heat for 40 minutes. Stir in cornstarch for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Heat stock in a 4 1/2-quart pan.
Add onions; cover and partially simmer for 40 minutes.
Skim froth as it appears.
Add salt and pepper.
Place bread in a casserole; ladle soup over bread and cover generously with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meats and drain.
Wash with hot water.
Add cheese and seasoning.
While warm, spread on party bread.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
Remove and put in plastic bags to store in freezer. Reheat in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: white chili
directions: Combine salsa and cheese in large sauce pan on stove over low heat stirring well to melt cheese. Add beans and chicken. Transfer to casserole dish and cook in 350° oven for 1 hour or prepare in crock-pot. Yields 6 servings.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Cook celery in water until tender (about 18 minutes).
Drain and save liquid (or use broth).
Saute onions in butter over low heat.
Drain oysters; add liquid to celery liquid (or broth).
Mix bread crumbs with poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Combine dry ingredients with onions, oysters and enough liquid to thoroughly moisten.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Cream margarine, confectioners sugar, Eagle Brand condensed milk and pecans.
Roll into small balls.
Melt paraffin wax and chocolate morsels.
Dip balls into chocolate and let cool on wax paper.

title: crunchy chicken casserole(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, saute celery in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and add next 8 ingredients.
Spoon into an ungreased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool.
Mix lemon cake mix, oil and eggs.
Add Jell-O to cake mixture.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: jello fruit fluff
directions: Fruit cocktail must be drained and rinsed.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine peas, eggs, cheese, pickles, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix salad dressing, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper for the dressing ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Stir. Chill and serve.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Spread baked crust with cream cheese mixture (sugar, vanilla and cream cheese).
Pile high with whole strawberries.
Pour strawberry sauce over top and refrigerate.
Best done early in the day it is to be served.
Cover generously with Cool Whip; garnish with large strawberries just before serving.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in a cup of water.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Drain pineapple and add to sugar and cream cheese mixture.
To this, add drained strawberries.
Add cool whip to jello and water.
Combine both mixtures and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: beef sopa
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain. Add chili and let simmer.
In a bowl, combine soups and Ro-Tel. Tear tortillas into 1/4's and layer in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle with a part of the cheese.
Layer meat mixture, tortillas, cheese and soup mixture, ending with a layer of soup. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute ground beef, onions and bell peppers until soft.
Add cooked rice, cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
To enhance flavor, mix all this up the night before.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350°
oven. This makes a moist dirty rice.

title: beef zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini whole until tender-crisp.
Drain and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Saute onions in shortening.
Add ground meat and brown lightly.
Drain.
Add crumbs, salt, pepper and oregano. Melt butter in pan; add flour.
Add milk; stir.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Place 1/2 of zucchini in 2-quart casserole, then 1/2 of beef, then cheese sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until marshmallows are melted.
Add gelatin to hot mixture and stir until dissolved.
Cream the cream cheese with a fork and stir the gelatin mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add mayonnaise to whipped cream.
Stir into thickened mixture.
Pour into a lightly oiled 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: mother's banbury tortes
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients 20 minutes, then add walnuts and orange juice.
Cook 20 minutes more.

title: honey buttered corn
directions: In mixing bowl, microwave margarine.
Stir in honey and parsley.
Set aside.
Wrap corn (each ear) in plastic wrap. Microwave corn on high for 8 to 16 minutes or until corn is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve honey butter with hot corn.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Make small marble sized pieces and put each piece in small muffin tins (ungreased).
Press pecan half into top of each piece.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Can also roll into log, chill and cut to cook on cookie sheet.

title: pizza hot dish(microwave)
directions: Put onions and green pepper in 2-quart casserole.
Crumble meat and cook on High, uncovered, until meat is set, stirring once. Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheeses and cover with casserole lid.
Micro on High 15 to 17 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Microwave on High uncovered 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheeses are melted.

title: stone ground corn bread
directions: Pour oil into cast-iron skillet.
Heat to the smoking point in 400° oven.
Meanwhile, combine cornmeal and other dry ingredients. Blend thoroughly.
When oil is hot, add buttermilk to dry ingredients and mix with stiff whisk.
Carefully remove skillet from oven and pour hot oil into batter, mixing with whisk while pouring.
Pour batter into skillet and return to oven.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and let rest for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: squash with green chilies
directions: Saute squash and onion in oil or margarine until tender.
Add milk, chilies, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 15 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat and add American cheese.
Cover and let stand several minutes off hot burner until cheese melts. (Slide off hot burner to let stand.) Serves 6.

title: hot carrot dip
directions: Mix together in small casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve hot!

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter together.
Add sugar, egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Roll thin; cut with cookie cutter and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: quick and easy "homemade" macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to box.
Mix in egg and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with more cheese. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Looks and tastes like homemade!

title: chicken with sour cream
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Frost with sour cream.
Sprinkle with just a little garlic salt.
Put onion and garlic croutons on top of this.
