Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger herb patties
directions: Mix together the beef, egg, salt and bread crumbs.
Saute onion in butter until transparent and add with herb mixture to meat and mix well.
Shape into 4 large or 6 medium patties.
Place under broiler and broil 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk together; add vanilla.

title: real orange drink
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then finish filling 2-quart pitcher with ice cubes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover. Remove from pan and reserve the broth.
Bone and dice the chicken. Add onion, celery, bouillon cubes, celery salt, salt (if you're using it), pepper, onion and seasoning to broth and simmer until tender. (I like them slightly crunchy.)
Add enough cornstarch to thicken and
a few drops of yellow food coloring if the sauce is gray looking.
Stir and cook until thickened. Add diced chicken to sauce and heat through.
That's it!

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water according to package directions.
Add cheese.
Mix until cheese melts.
Add butter or margarine, egg, seasoned salt and Tabasco.
Mix and bake at 350°.

title: brownies (white)
directions: Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 32 squares.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add salt and mustard.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix in order and roll into balls.
Next, roll into more powdered sugar (1/2 box).
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix very well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until cake tests done.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all together.
Pour and pat down into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dill sauce
directions: Mix mayonnaise, olives and dill weed.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with water; bring to a boil and cook about 3 minutes, stirring.
Add strawberries.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook lentils 30 minutes in water.
Braise onion and garlic in oil; add to lentils with vegetables.
Cook 45 minutes; add seasoning, margarine and lemon juice.

title: quick cheese danish
directions: Spread one can of rolls flat and pinch perforations together. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread on crust.
Take other can of rolls.
Pinch perforations and lay over cheese layer.
Brush top with beaten egg white.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, chopped nuts and cinnamon together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: my ultimate paella #3
directions: Place sausages in 12-inch heavy skillet.
Add enough cold water to cover them completely.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for around 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels; season with salt and pepper.
In a heavy 12-inch skillet, heat 1/4 cup of the olive oil.
Add the chicken, skin side down, and brown, turning pieces with tongs.
When golden brown, remove to a platter.
Place the remaining 1/4 cup olive oil in 12-inch skillet.
Add the onions, garlic, bell pepper and tomato.
Cook briskly until most of the liquid in the pan evaporates.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package in a sheet cake pan.
Cool. Crumble 1/2 cake mixture (cooked) in bottom of a punch bowl.
Add 1/2 cherry pie filling, 1/2 of the pineapple, 1/2 of the prepared instant vanilla pudding and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the coconut.
Repeat with rest of the ingredients.

title: congealed salad
directions: Put Jell-O in flat dish (8 x 11-inch).
Add 2 cups boiling water to Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Drain pineapple and add juice to Jell-O.
Mix pineapple, cottage cheese, mayonnaise, condensed milk and nuts or celery together.
Add to Jell-O. Refrigerate until set.
Serves 12.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix Good Seasons mix according to package directions.
Pour over all other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chicken soup
directions: Slice chicken breast strips lengthwise, then cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
In a 4-quart saucepan, saut chicken in olive oil over medium-high heat until it begins to brown.
Add onions and garlic. Continue cooking and stirring constantly until the onions soften. Stir in the chicken broth and water.
Add pasta, bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in mixed vegetables, parsley, basil and pepper.
Return to boil, then simmer about 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 cups.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Refrigerate until it is slightly set.
Mix together cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add to congealed jello.
Refrigerate and let mixture slightly congeal again.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Let stand, stirring occasionally. Fold in whipping cream and return to refrigerator until set.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add flour; work in good.
Add nuts and make into large ball.
Chill about 15 minutes.
Remove; make small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until bottom slightly brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: wine drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk, molasses alternately with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion together.
Add dry soup mix and boiling water.
Add rice. Cook for 45 minutes in electric skillet or oven.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain well and pour into a casserole dish.
Microwave butter on High until melted. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Microwave at High for 5 1/2 to 6 minutes, stirring with a fork every minute until thickened.
Stir in cheese until completely melted.
Stir sauce into drained macaroni; mix well.
Microwave at Medium for 7 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Soften butter and cheese; cream together.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into the size of a marble and flatten with fork dipped in water.
Cover and bake on an ungreased sheet for 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then alternate flour and remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer for 5 minutes. Add pineapple and stir with spoon.
Do not beat pineapple in. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 10 minutes longer if not done. Bake in tube pan.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Prepare Alfredo sauce as directed. Place a bed of rice on serving dish; arrange chunks of chicken over top.
Sprinkle pimentos as desired.
Pour sauce over mound; garnish with sugar peas.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt chips in doubler boiler; stir in the noodles.
Spoon out on wax paper and let cool.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Make crust of flour, margarine and nuts.
Mix and press into bottom of casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool crust completely.
Make filling of cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix and layer over crust.
Mix pudding mix with milk and beat until thick.
Spread over cream cheese.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
You may sprinkle with more nuts on top.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In an oblong pan, layer ingredients as written.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: maggie's sweet potato bread(club member: terah smith)
directions: Blend well with a mixer. Pour into a Pyrex dish. Bake in a 350° preheated oven 30 to 45 minutes. Serve as you desire.

title: japanese-style cabbage roll
directions: Boil leaves of cabbage to be flexible, one by one in boiling water.
Slice off the cores of the leaves.
Slice leeks, mushrooms and cores of cabbage.
Slice the carrot and make flowers.
Mix up the minced meat, adding leeks, mushrooms and cores with salt, eggs and bread crumbs.
Make 8 balls and wrap each ball with leaves of cabbage to make rolls.
Put the rolls and carrot-flowers in the pot with water together with bouillon cubes and heat.
Add sake and soy sauce and boil for 20 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons of water until smooth and add to soup and cook until clear and thickened.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared crust in pan.
Cover
with top crust and crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust
with
small slits and brush with beaten egg, if desired. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar and spread in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip over cooled crust.
Mix jello and water; add frozen strawberries.
Let thicken and pour over Cool Whip layer.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough into a 12-inch circle and bake on a pizza pan until lightly browned.
Remove giant "cookie" to a decorative serving plate and build pizza as follows.

title: perk punch
directions: Put juices, brown sugar, water and salt in the bottom of a 30 to 36 cup perk pot.
Put spices in the top basket and let perk.

title: yackety-yack chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt on piece of waxed paper to mix well.
Beat together butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar in bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat to combine.
Stir in pecans, chocolate and raisins.

title: aunt dorothy's pistachio dessert
directions: Mix cottage cheese and pineapple.
Stir in pudding.
Combine well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in marshmallows.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the corned beef.
Roll mixture into ball, then roll in the corned beef until covered.
Chill. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: banana punch
directions: The amounts of meat can vary in accordance with other food served.
I have found these figures to be low unless someone is going to serve the meat.
However, it is better to have some extra.
Should also have some instant potato flakes on hand in case the potatoes run low.

The 6 gallons of milk is based on serving milk with the meal, so there again, you can estimate how much of the milk is to be used directly in the preparation of the meal, allowing some extra in case someone does want to drink milk. The 5 large cakes mentioned is the equivalent of 3 large pans of bars which are generally used for dessert; that amount is usually sufficient.

title: crumb top coffee cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in 1/4 cup margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Add baking powder, cinnamon and salt; cut in remaining margarine and add combined milk and egg, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: marinade for grilled chicken breast
directions: Lay chicken breast up in a baking dish and sprinkle ingredients in order listed.
Turn breast part down in juice and marinate overnight.
Then cook on a grill.
Tastes great!

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine 1/4 cup flour and caramel topping.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, rolled oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and butter; mix until crumbly. Press 2/3 of crumbly mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle remaining crumbly mixture over caramel.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes, cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Pour eggs, cornstarch and sugar; mix together.
Add a little milk at a time.
After mixing thoroughly, add salt.
Cook slowly over low heat until thickened.
After pudding is off stove, add vanilla and butter.
Cool, then add Cool Whip.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Butter muffin pans.
Mix all ingredients together and put in muffin pans.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup and wine.
Pour over chicken in uncovered, greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Bring ingredients to boil and pour over pickles in the jar. Turn jar over to mix every day.
Best after 3 days.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter.
Mix peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and 10x sugar together.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread with a knife over the peanut butter mixture. Cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread one can each of chili and corn over bottom of 8-inch square cooking pan or casserole dish.
Spread half the chili salsa and half the sour cream over this.
Use cayenne pepper next if you like it hot.
Cover with a layer of Fritos or tortilla chips. Repeat this with a second layer exactly the same.
Cover dish with Fritos or tortilla chips and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, until heated through.
Serves 4 to 6, depending on appetite.

title: baby back pork ribs
directions: Pour enough barbecue sauce on the bottom of a large rectangular Pyrex dish so you can spread the sauce around to just cover the bottom.
Place two racks of baby back ribs, side by side, on top of the sauce.
Pour the remaining sauce on top of your ribs.

title: quick pizza sticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease large cookie sheet.
Unroll dough onto cookie sheet and brush with margarine.
In a small bowl, put remaining ingredients and sprinkle evenly over dough. With a pizza cutter, cut dough into 12 (1-inch) strips, then each in half across the width.
Do not separate.
Bake for 10 to 13 minutes.
Serve immediately with pizza sauce, if desired.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Blend
butter,	margarine
and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, then
flour
and milk alternately.	Add flavoring.	Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with the cream of mushroom soup.
Add the grated cheese. Top with the Tater Tots.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover and brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add taco seasoning mix and Ranch dressing.
Add all remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly. Serve with Fritos or nachos.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
You can also add sour cream.

title: easy zucchini bake(microwave; vegetable)
directions: Put diced zucchini in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 3 tablespoons margarine; cover.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Mix beaten eggs, salt, pepper and Accent.
Pour over baked zucchini.
Top with 1/2 cheese.
Bake 5 minutes uncovered.
Stir after 5 minutes; add the rest of the cheese and top with French fried onions.
Cook 5 more minutes uncovered.

title: black-eyed pea salsa
directions: In a bowl, combine first 12 ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: 6 cups.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a full, rolling boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: summertime iced tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts. Debone and cut into bite size pieces. Place meat in 10 x 13 casserole. Save broth. Mix together sour cream, mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup. Pour over chicken. Mix together cornbread dressing mix and chicken flavor dressing mix. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Then mix chicken broth, oleo and vegetable mix together and bring to a boil. Pour over casserole and bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor dressing mix

title: fried squash cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients in large skillet. Add water for boiling. Cook until mixture is tender. Make sure mixture is cooked down with little fluid. Set aside.

title: sweet pickles the easy way(heritage recipe)
directions: Use 1 qt. dill pickles, sliced and drained, put in bowl.
On top of pickles put other ingredients.
Let stand 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Put back in jar.
Turn upside down once in a while.
Put in refrigerator to become crisp.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook corn bread by directions on package.
Crumble bread and mix with other ingredients, except oleo and cheese.
Melt butter in casserole dish and pour in other mixture .
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put grated cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: cookies from cake mix
directions: Mix all together.
Add nuts, raisins, coconut, granola, flavor chips or whatever you like.
Spoon drops of dough on cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully!!

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Combine beans, celery, onion, salt and Miracle Whip.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir in other ingredients.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: country fresh biscuits
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 400°.

title: potato soup(modern)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water with salt.
When soft, run through strainer.
Boil milk with onions; remove onions and add milk slowly to potatoes, mixing well with whisk. Melt half the butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed, then add to soup.
Boil 1 minute; add remaining butter and sprinkle with parsley.
Thin with hot milk, if desired.

title: cream broccoli and cheese
directions: Mix soup, milk, Miracle Whip and lemon juice together.
Layer liquid mixture over broccoli spears.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry whip
directions: Mix good condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and pie filling.
Mix and chill.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers well and pack into quart jars.
Add above ingredients to each quart jar.
Finish filling jar with boiling water and seal.
Note:
Dill seed may be used.
I turn jars upside down until cold.

title: salmon chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and saute onions and celery until transparent, but not brown.
Add 1 tablespoon flour and mix into sauteed onions and celery.
Now add half and half and bring to a boil.
Reduce flame to simmer and add flaked salmon and mashed potatoes.
Stir until mixture is smooth, then add Herbes de Provence.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(I added about 1/2 teaspoon of oregano, basil and parsley instead of Herbes de Provence when I couldn't find them.)

title: lamb kabobs(healthy recipe)
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add lamb and toss until coated.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight. Preheat barbecue or broiler for 10 minutes.
Onto two 12-inch skewers, alternately thread half of the lamb, onion/shallots and cherry tomatoes.
Brush the shallots and tomatoes with the yogurt mixture.
Cook the kabobs for 8 minutes, turning occasionally until lamb is browned.
Good with brown rice, couscous, noodles and a salad.
Serves 2.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in hot oil; add onion and garlic; saute about 3 minutes.
Stir in chili powder and cook 1 minute.
Add water, tomato sauce, cumin, salt, pepper and red pepper seasoning.
Heat to boiling, then cook over low heat for 2 1/2 hours.
Then mix together flour and corn meal; stir well into chili.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: california taco boats
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
Drain.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, and stirring occasionally for 10 minutes or until most of the liquid evaporates and the mixture thickens.
Halve, seed and peel avocados.
Spoon meat mixture over avocado halves.
Top each with shredded cheese.
Place under broiler and heat until cheese melts.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a large heavy skillet.
Add consomme or beef broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until beef is tender. Blend cornstarch and water; stir gradually into the stew.
Cook, stirring constantly, until gravy thickens and boils. Cook 1 minute more. Serve over rice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: japanese chicken salad
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool, bone chicken and shred.
Set aside.

title: hello dollie cookies
directions: Melt butter in 8 1/4 x 8 1/4-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and place in pan of butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels with peanut butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until well blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press half of mixture into buttered 11 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Chill.
Stir over hot water semi-sweet chocolate morsels, sifted confectioners sugar (10x), butter and water until chocolate melts.
Spread over chilled mixture in pan and top with other half of cereal mixture.
Chill and cut in squares.
I add walnuts to cereal mixture.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in order: pie filling, pineapple, coconut, cake mix and pecans in 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
When you get to the butter, grate it over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: wild rice and chicken soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until onion is soft and limp.
Stir in flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat until the mixture is bubbly.
Gradually add chicken and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream and cooked wild rice.

title: yummy yellow cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Immediately after taking from the oven, prick many times with a toothpick.
Then pour the hot milk with sugar dissolved in milk over the cake. Cover with Dream Whip or Cool Whip mixed with coconut.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients n bowl; mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: baked cheese shrimp custard
directions: Remove crusts from bread, spread with butter and cut in 1 inch squares.
Cut the cheese in thin slices, devein the shrimp.
In a greased 2 quart casserole lay alternate layers of bread, shrimp and cheese.
Combine eggs, salt, paprika and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a silver knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: nova scotia salmon pie(bob hall's version)
directions: Mix the milk, margarine, flour,
pepper and cheese over low heat until cheese melts.
Add salmon, celery, carrot and mushrooms. Blend gently.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Mashed potatoes may be substituted for biscuits.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients but marshmallows and heat in microwave to taste.
Put in marshmallows when hot and serve hot.

title: spin fin fish
directions: Thaw spinach in microwave. layer filets flat with inside up. Salt and pepper generously.
Squeeze juice from spinach and place small amount in center of each filet.
Roll and secure with toothpick.
Place in Pam coated baking dish.
Place 1 Tbsp.
Hidden Valley ranch dressing on top of each filet.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil.
Brown under broiler.

title: cajun gumbo(chicken sausage)
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery.
Heat 1 cup cooking oil over medium heat.
Add 3/4 cup flour; stir, scraping bottom, until dark brown.
Do not scorch flour.
Immediately add 1/2 of all vegetables, stirring until onion is soft.
Add 1/2 gallon water; let boil 30 minutes.
Add remainder of vegetables.
Add sausage, 1 tablespoon red pepper, 1 tablespoons McCormick Season-All and 6 chicken cubes.
Let boil 30 minutes.
Add chicken and okra; let boil 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add seafood and boil 15 minutes more, then serve.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Blend vanilla and chocolate into creamed mixture.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with water; beat after each addition.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with chocolate chips; arrange nut halves over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: joes to go
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Add garlic salt, pepper, chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.
May be frozen along with buns and Joes are ready to go any time needed.

title: quiche with self-forming crust
directions: Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cheese into lightly greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add milk, flour, baking powder, salt, pepper and onions.
Mix for 4 minutes on low speed.
Pour mixture over cheese and sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese over liquid mixture in pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Surface will be lightly browned and puffy.
Serves 12.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes. Remove tea bags, strain and serve hot.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: jet's apple chip cake
directions: Blend together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add nuts, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and 2 cups of flour.
Batter will be very thick. Mix in apples and last cup of flour with a wooden spatula or spoon.
Turn batter into a lightly greased and dusted 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clam digger's dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream and clam liquid until smooth and well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Serve with potato chips. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate bonbons candy
directions: Combine peanut butter, powdered sugar, cherries and walnuts; roll into balls.
Melt chocolate chips, unsweetened chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and lay on wax paper.
I usually double recipe.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fry sausage loosely.
Drain on paper towels.
Cool.
Crumble in small pieces.
In a large bowl, put 2 cups Bisquick, cooled crumbled sausage and grated cheese.
Mix together.
Add the milk.
Mix; mixture should be wet.
If needed, add a little more milk.
Drop by spoonfuls onto sprayed (Pam) cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: fried cheese grits party bites
directions: Bring water and salt to boil in large saucepan.
Slowly stir in grits; cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of grits mixture into egg; return all to saucepan.
Add cheese, paprika and hot sauce; blend well.
Pour mixture into greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Cool; cover and place in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Cut into 1-inch cubes and coat with flour.
Deep fat fry until cubes are golden brown and float to the top.
Drain well.
Best served warm.
Good when dipped in sweet and sour sauce.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: You can substitute chocolate pudding with vanilla pudding.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream oleo and peanut butter.
Mix in sugar and beat by hand until smooth.
Roll into balls and put toothpicks in.
Freeze an hour.
Dip in melted semi-sweet chocolate up to toothpick until you get a buckeye look.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in your favorite salad dressing sprinkled with Accent for 1 hour at least.
Broil on broiler rack until golden brown on both sides (about 8 minutes per side).

title: deep chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add water.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange nuts and coconut in sugar mixture.
Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour batter over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes until cake springs back when touched lightly.
Let stand 5 minutes for topping to begin to set.
Then turn upside-down onto a large platter or a cookie sheet.
Serve pieces of cake topped with whipped cream.

title: crunchy oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine cereal, chopped parsley, seasoning and lemon pepper in a shallow dish. Brush chicken with yogurt and roll in cereal mixture. Place chicken on broiler pan, coated with cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes or until done. Serves 4.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar together and place into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; let cool.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Add salt, pepper, whole tomatoes and tomato paste.
Fill can that had whole tomatoes with water and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Use over large box of cooked spaghetti (16 ounces).

title: spaghetti carbona
directions: Boil water and cook spaghetti.
Fry crumbled sausage; drain. Saute onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Stir in jar of spaghetti sauce.
Mix all ingredients, except eggs, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and Parmesan cheese.
Stir egg mixture into warm spaghetti-noodle mixture.

title: orange almond salad
directions: In a screw top jar mix first 5 ingredients and shake well until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Combine next 5 ingredients into bowl, pour dressing on top and serve immediately.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Beat oleo until fluffy.
Add melted and cooled chocolate, powdered sugar and vanilla; continue beating.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each egg.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Chill before serving.

title: individual chicken-popover casseroles
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease four 16 ounce casseroles.
Cook and stir celery and onion in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender. Stir in chicken, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and soup.
Heat to boiling, over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Divide among casseroles.

title: chicken picante
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in oil until browned.
Add jar of picante to chicken.
Slowly add chunks of Velveeta.
Stir until cheese melts.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit cobbler(use any kind of fruit.)
directions: Put bag of fruit in baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and sugar together.
Mix in egg and butter; smash with a fork.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: "hot" chinese mustard
directions: Stir together equal parts of dry mustard and beer.
Let set a minute before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage.
Roll crescent rolls flat in baking dish. Sprinkle sausage and cheese on top of rolls.
Beat eggs lightly and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until eggs are done.

title: congealed apricot salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir just enough to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat and stir in pineapple and baby food.
Set aside to cool.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder with milk until smooth.
Pour into melted butter (do not stir).
Spread fruit evenly on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream
directions: In large
saucepan,
beat
egg whites with 1 cup sugar, gradually adding
sugar over eggs until all sugar is added and well dissolved.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take stems off mushrooms and chop fine.
Saute in a frying pan with butter or margarine.
Put stems in bowl and add other ingredients; mix well.
Melt the stick of butter and brush on mushroom caps.
Stuff caps with mixture and brush top with butter. Place on a greased tin and put in broiler.
Broil for 3 to 3 minutes.

title: garlic and ginger marinade for grilled chicken
directions: Mix and refrigerate for up to 2 weeks.
Marinate chicken overnight in refrigerator before grilling.
Lightly butter chicken while grilling to keep moist and tender.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour (2 times) with salt. Add to other ingredients; mix well.
Add whipping cream, small amounts at a time; mix well.
Bake in tube pan (not Bundt pan), greased and floured, at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and place in large casserole dish. Melt 1 stick margarine and combine with 1 roll of Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil noodles in 8 quarts of water with 1/4 cup salt and 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Boil for 15 minutes or until tender, then drain.
Heat in skillet 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Add and cook until browned, ground beef.
In a baking dish pour 1/2 cup meat sauce into bottom.
Top with a layer of noodles, 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese, sliced, then add ground beef and 1 hard-boiled egg, sliced.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the grated Parmesan combined with pepper.
Top with 1/2 cup Ricotta cheese.
Beginning with sauce, repeat layers, ending with Ricotta cheese.
Top Ricotta cheese with 1/2 cup sauce.
Arrange over this remaining lasagne noodles.
Top with more sauce.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut into 2 inch squares and serve with remaining sauce.
Lasagne can be frozen after it is cooked. Reheat 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: grammy's bluefish chowder
directions: Poach fillets in 2 cups water 8 to 10 minutes.
Fry pork until crisp in large saucepan.
Remove and reserve.
Add onion and pepper to fat and cook until tender.
Add fish liquid and potatoes.
Simmer covered 10 minutes.
Add soup, milk and fish, stirring to blend.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: squash crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into patties.
Fry in hot oil.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Let set a few minutes. Then make into small flat balls and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Makes about 12.

title: beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a covered roaster.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Keep covered until done.

title: frozen pink salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze for 1 hour or refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Mix in egg and buttermilk.
Mix together oats, flour, baking powder, salt and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in bananas.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine margarine, evaporated milk and sugar together in a pot.
Heat over med. high heat until boiling, stirring occasionally.
Once mixture starts to boil, stir constantly for 5 minutes.
Check to make sure mixture forms soft ball stage. Remove mixture from stove.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 inch pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: l.b.j. cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the next 3 ingredients; spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle coconut over this.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Spread in pie plate and cover with chives.
Blend milk, eggs and Bisquick. Pour over chives.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and tomato.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes more.
Let cool 5 minutes. Serve.

title: blackberry rolls
directions: Serve hot or with powdered sugar.

title: pork and beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove pan from stove and pour off excess grease.
Brown onion in the pan where you fried bacon, then add brown sugar and catsup.
Let this simmer until mixed well. Put pork and beans in a casserole dish and pour the brown sugar, onion and catsup mixture over the pork and beans.
Top with bacon. Put in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to an hour.
Very good with hamburgers or barbecue chicken.

title: deep dish chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degree.
In 2 1/2 quart oval casserole dish mix 2 cans soup, 2 pkg. frozen vegetables and chicken.
Mix milk, egg and baking mix.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: devil dogs
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on baking sheet. Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Put Devil Dogs together with filling.

title: quick pasta salad primavera
directions: Prepare garden and regular spirals together according to package directions; drain.
In a large bowl, combine spirals and remaining ingredients; toss to mix.
Cover over; chill thoroughly. Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas cut cookies
directions: Beat butter for 1 minute.
Add 1 cup flour; beat.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Add remaining flour (1 cup). Divide dough in half; cover with Saran Wrap.
Chill 1 hour and roll out and cut 1/8-inch thick (not too thin; they will burn on edges).
Cook 6 to 7 minutes at 375°.

title: star bright aspic
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add juice, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Congeal.
Top with cheese and olives.

title: homemade brandied fruit
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1-quart glass container with a loose-fitting lid. Stir 3 or 4 times on the first day with a wooden spoon and once a day thereafter.
After 7 days, the fruit has made a start.
Every 2 weeks, add 1 cup thoroughly drained fruit and 1 cup granulated sugar.
Fruit can be used 24 hours after each addition of ingredients.
Use as a sauce over ice cream, relish with ham, etc.
Always keep 1 cup for starter.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to instructions on cake box. Allow to cool.
Spread unfrozen strawberries over cake. Pick with fork to allow juice to soak in.
Spread Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir baking soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.
Beat thoroughly, then add vanilla and almond extract.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until golden.

title: sourdough starter for sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients into a fairly thick rubbery consistency. Place in a bowl and cover with a cloth.
Let stand in a warm place for 2 or 3 days until fermented.
Thereafter, store in the refrigerator, always leaving 1 cup of starter.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Pour milk over oats.
Set aside 5 minutes.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients into bowl.
Stir in soaked oats, eggs and oil.
Drop by spoonful onto a lightly greased hot griddle.

title: moussaka(meat sauce)
directions: Saute onion, meat and garlic in hot butter in a 3 1/2-quart Dutch oven, stirring until brown (about 10 minutes).
Add herbs, spices and tomato sauce and bring to boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Halve unpared eggplants lengthwise; slice crosswise a 1/2-inch or less thick.
Place in bottom of broiler pan; sprinkle lightly with salt and brush lightly with melted butter.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 4 minutes each side or until golden.
Next, make cream sauce.

title: ratatouille
directions: Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth and cut off rough edges.
Cube eggplant and cut zucchini into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut peppers into 1-inch pieces.
In heavy saucepan, heat oil.
Add onions, garlic, mushroom and cook briskly for several minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to boiling, cover and simmer gently for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain in colander; save liquid in another pan and boil down by half.
Pour over vegetables and serve.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool cake.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 16.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour, baking powder and salt sifted together, alternately with milk. Add flavoring. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°. Use pan that is well-greased and floured. Let cool 5 to 10 minutes, then place in box.

title: ron's blueberry banana pancakes
directions: Beat egg in a medium bowl.
Add the buttermilk and mix well. Stir in the Bisquick until well blended.
Mash the ripe banana and add to mixture.
Gently fold in the blueberries.
Pour about 1/4 cup onto a hot griddle; cook until edges are dry.
Turn and cook until brown.
Try spreading peanut butter and syrup on top for a great tasting alternative.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: shrimp with warm remoulade
directions: Rub the shrimp with the Essence.
Heat the oil in a skillet over medium
heat. Cook the shrimp for 3 to 4 minutes. Add the wine and cook for 1 minute. Add the Remoulade Sauce and simmer for about 2 minutes. Add the green onions.
Spoon the sauce over cooked pasta and serve immediately. Yield: 4 first-course servings.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mealy.
Work in water gradually to form a pastry-like dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll as thin as possible.
Cut into 2 or 3-inch squares.
Fry one by one in hot oil (370°).
They should puff up as they brown and should be turned during the frying so the second side can also puff.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 20 or 30.

title: tagliarini, zucchini, lemon, pine nuts and herbs
directions: Slice zucchini diagonally into pieces about same thickness as the pasta.
Line up slices, cut in narrow matchsticks.
Each one will be tipped with green or gold.
Chop fresh herbs, not too finely.
Remove thin strip of lemon peel and cut into fine slivers. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in small pan and add pine nuts.
Cook until begins to color, then add shallots.
Cook until shallots are soft and pine nuts are browned.
Transfer to wide bowl and add rest of oil, capers, lemon peel, sun-dried tomatoes and herbs.
Season with salt, freshly ground black pepper and 1/2 teaspoon of lemon juice to taste.
Add salt to boiling water; drop in zucchini and cook 1 minute.
Scoop out; shake off water and add to the bowl with other ingredients.
Next, cook pasta; scoop it out and add it to bowl as well.
Toss with pair of tongs so that the noodles are coated with oil and herbs.
Serve with cheese passed separately. For wine, serve a Sauvignon Blanc.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix in oleo, melted.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut, butterscotch chips and chocolate chips on top.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk all over the top.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars after cooled.

title: coke cake
directions: Put the flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Combine the oleo, cocoa and Coke; bring to a boil.
Pour into flour and sugar mixture.
Add the buttermilk, soda, vanilla, eggs and miniature marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: candied yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin and split cooked potatoes. Arrange in casserole; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Pour syrup and orange juice over potatoes and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar and just enough milk to spread.
Spread on cookies.
Put back in freezer until firm.
Cut into small squares.
Store in freezer.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Blend cheese, butter, salt and vanilla together.
Stir in sugar.
Pour coconut into bowl and roll butter in coconut.
Place on cookie sheet and let set overnight or completely chilled.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cool summer salad
directions: Place cucumbers and mushrooms in colander; set aside to drain. Mix all remaining ingredients.
Put cucumbers and mushrooms into a large bowl and stir in yogurt mix.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: famous cob salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: chicken baked with mushrooms
directions: Place pieces of chicken in large baking dish or roast dish. Place salt, pepper, garlic and onion (chopped) over chicken.
Add some water around chicken.
Cover in mushroom soup.
Cook in oven for 1 hour or until chicken is ready.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients to form dough.
Roll to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut the biscuits and brush with butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Melt butter and stir in sour cream, cheese, soup, onion, salt and pepper.
Blend all with the thawed hash brown potatoes and turn into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and mix with 1 cup crushed corn flakes.
Spread over top of potatoes.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Mix with hands well.
Roll into balls, nickle size.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm.

title: basic cobbler
directions: Melt butter; mix with already mixed flour, sugar and milk. Pour sugared fruit on top of this batter which has been poured into Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple pecan delight
directions: Sift dry ingredients, mix with remaining ingredients. Bake in greased 8 x 10 inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven. Top with whip cream or ice cream.

title: beef with yorkshire pudding
directions: Place roast, fat side up, in a roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° until meat thermometer registers 140° rare, 160° medium or 170° for well-done.
Allow 3 1/2 hours for rare, 4 hours for medium and 4 3/4 hours for well-done.
Remove meat from pan, cover and keep warm.
Reserve 1/4 cup meat drippings.
Increase oven temperature to 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add stuffing mix to butter and can of broth, mixing well.
In bottom of casserole layer chicken.
Mix both cans of soup and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with onion (optional). Layer stuffing mix on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit whip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let cool, then enjoy.

title: salmon puff
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in a large casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Butter each slice of bread.
Top with cheese.
Beat eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard together.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before cooking, mix soup and 1/2 cup milk together and pour over egg mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. (Sausage may be browned and crumbled over top.)

title: squaw corn
directions: Cut luncheon meat in julienne strips and brown in the fat. Combine all other ingredients and add to meat.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the eggs are just set.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: apples stuffed with sausage
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Core apples, but do not go all the way through. Season inside of cored apples and stuff sausage into hole. Bake at 350° in oven for 35 minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: fruit n juice shake
directions: Combine the ingredients in a blender and blend for about 30 seconds.
"No fat."

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Chop green pepper, onion and garlic; saute.
Cook ground beef; drain.
Mix with pepper, onion and garlic; stir in tomato sauce, cover and simmer.
Cook spaghetti in boiling water.
Drain.
Add meat mixture, stirring until blended.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle sliced olives and mushrooms over top.
Add grated cheese over this.
Pour more mixture; repeat procedure.
Bake casserole until contents are thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This can be made ahead of time and stored in freezer.
Makes a large casserole.

title: chicken dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together then refrigerate.

title: low-fat beaten biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt and milk together.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray. Drop dough by large spoonfuls into pan.
Spray tops of biscuits lightly with cooking spray. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix the last four ingredients together.
Let stand a few hours. Much better if it stands overnight.
Add the cauliflower, radishes and onion to dressing.

title: pork chops with hominy
directions: Fry on griddle or grill pork chops outdoors; salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Make or purchase your favorite tomato sauce.
Heat, then add scallops or shrimp or both, cooked or fresh; simmer until done. Serve over cooked rice or pasta.

title: mama's mini-cinnis
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Unroll crescent rolls and separate each dough portion along center perforation to form 4 rectangles. Press diagonal perforations to seal. Stir together butter and next 3 ingredients. Spread evenly over 1 side of each rectangle. Sprinkle with pecans. Roll up jelly roll fashion, starting at long end. Gently cut each log into 6 (1-inch thick) slices, using a serrated knife. Place rolls, 1/4-inch apart, into 2 (8-inch) greased cake pans, placing 3 in the center. Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pans. Cool 5 to 10 minutes. Stir together powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. Drizzle over warm rolls. Makes 2 dozen.

title: scalloped meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup milk, egg and onion and form into meatballs.
Fry in pan until done and brown.
Put into dish.
Use the fryings and add 1 cup or more of milk; use enough to make gravy to cover meatballs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put meatballs into gravy and simmer until ready to eat.

title: liver casserole(nourishing, filling.)
directions: Cook spinach. Remove spinach when done.
Let drain in colander. Cook noodles in same water. At the same time, cook liver and cut into bite size pieces.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for oil; stir oil into other ingredients slowly.
Can be used as a dressing or pour over chicken or pork chops and bake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion and water in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with lid and microwave on High for 9 to 10 minutes, or until squash is tender, stirring after 4 minutes.
Mash squash mixture with potato masher.
Add remaining ingredients (except paprika); stir well and cover.
Microwave on Medium for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cookies-n-cream
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dip each cookie in milk and make a bottom layer of cookies.
Next, layer with whipped cream, then repeat until dish is full.
The final layer is chocolate chip cookies crumbled on top.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour, then serve cold.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavoring, beating after each addition until smooth.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) well-greased pans.
Bake at 350°

title: best cake
directions: Mix the eggs, flour, baking soda, vanilla, sugar, chopped walnuts and crushed pineapple with a spoon. Put in greased bar cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine all except 1/4 cup crumbs and margarine.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Blend 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons margarine and brown in skillet.
Sprinkle over top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grilled grouper
directions: Heat grill to medium. In a very small saucepan, melt butter. Add lemon juice and garlic. Place grouper, skin side down, on grill (do not turn). Baste with butter sauce approximately 3 times while grilling. Grilling time will be approximately 9 to 15 minutes, depending upon the thickness of the grouper.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs to blend.
Add salad oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat to thick and foamy.
Stir in with spoon coarsely shredded zucchini and drained crushed pineapple.
In another bowl, combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and raisins. Stir into zucchini mix to blind.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for one hour.
Cool ten minutes and remove from pan.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place meat on heavy-duty foil.
Cover meat with onions and rest of ingredients except mushrooms.
Seal tightly and bake 3 hours or until tender.
Slice meat; thicken gravy and add mushrooms.

title: friendship cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 to 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine dry cake and pudding mixes, oil, eggs and vanilla. Fold in nuts and fruit.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: orange-mincemeat bavarian pie
directions: Crumble mincemeat into a saucepan, add 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: chocolate mint coffee
directions: Beat cream with sugar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Fold in grated chocolate.
Pour hot coffee evenly into 4 mugs and add 2 tablespoons of Schnapps to each.
Spoon on whipped cream.
Garnish with chocolate curls and serve immediately.

title: plum sauce
directions: Cook as Sure-Jell directs.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix dressing with mayonnaise.
Pour over Swiss cheese.
Layer all as listed into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with the rye bread.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles by directions; drain and set aside.
Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Add fennel seed and oregano and mix. Place half of noodles in baking dish.
Add meat and half of cheese.
Add rest of noodles and top with cheese.
Add Creole sauce all over that.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: boiled chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until soft and you have nice broth (about 4 quarts).
Remove chicken and cool.
Mix flour, eggs, Crisco, salt and pepper to form dough.
Separate dough into 5 pieces.
Roll each piece to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut dough into squares.
Bring broth to a boil and drop dough squares into broth, one at a time. Add potatoes, onion and parsley.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes until dough is soft.
Add cut up chicken and serve.

title: drechter kucka (funnel cake)
directions: Beat egg; add milk. Sift salt, sugar, flour and baking powder together. Add egg and milk. Beat until smooth. Pour batter into funnel, holding finger over the bottom. Allow batter to run out of funnel into deep fat, 375° and
make swirls in fat from center out. Cakes may be any size. Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel. Dip in confectioners sugar.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar and beat hard.
Stir in vanilla, lemon juice and peel.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Put small amount from teaspoon onto ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen small rich cookies.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except crab meat and blend until smooth.
Add crab meat and place into a baking casserole. Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and paprika and bake uncovered in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli, cauliflower and pea salad
directions: Slice broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle dill weed on top.

title: tuna tostadas
directions: In a small bowl, combine sour cream with chili powder.
Set aside for 20 minutes.
Brush tortillas lightly with sour cream mixture.
Spoon 1/4 of the tuna on each.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Drizzle with remaining sour cream mixture.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Mix all together and smooth into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes and place in casserole.
Pour mushroom soup over meat and sprinkle with onion soup and wine. Bake in 225° oven for 4 hours.

title: never fail jelly roll
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Sift small amount of flour over egg mixture; fold in.
Continue until all flour is used.
Add vanilla.
Line jelly roll pan with wax paper (bottom and sides).
Pour in batter; spread evenly.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Remove cake to a damp cloth; spread on jelly and roll.
Trim ends.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix half bread crumbs and half Parmesan cheese together to coat chicken; set aside.
Cut chicken into small strips or pieces. Roll in coating mixture.
(I usually dip my chicken in milk or beaten egg to help hold coating.)
Get grease hot in frying pan. Cook chicken fast, until brown on both sides.

title: oatmeal phinsees
directions: Cream together butter, sugars and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Watch carefully.
Lightly does it.

title: low fat taco soup
directions: Brown meat. Drain and rinse with hot water to remove fat. Saute onion with meat.
Put in crock pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 4 to 5 hours on low setting.

title: creamy carrot cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Reserve 1 1/2 cups dry cake mix for filling.
Combine remaining dry cake mix and melted butter in large mixer bowl at low speed. Stir in chopped pecans.
Firmly press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then set in freezer for 5 minutes or until bottom of pan is cold.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt the white chocolate and pour over the mixture of raisins, peanuts and pretzels. Spread into a pan and place in the freezer for about 5 minutes or until the chocolate is set.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased, hot muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Butter tops.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Place half of apples in pie shell.
Squeeze 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice over them and top with half of the sugar-flour mixture.
Arrange rest of apples on top.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice and rest of sugar-flour mixture over apples.
Dot with butter.
Place top pastry over all.
Seal edges of crust, make 3 or 4 slices near center.
Brush top crust with a little beaten egg yolk and melted butter to glaze.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm topped with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: homemade chocolate candy
directions: Mix together cocoa and sugar, then milk in your skillet.
Mix well.
Cook on stove on medium-high heat.
Stir constantly.
Let cook and stir occasionally, 30 to 40 minutes.
When it starts to get hard around edges, remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Stir well.
Beat in skillet until it gets thick, then pour onto platter, greased with margarine.
Let cool for 20 minutes and cut into pieces.

title: pea salad
directions: Thaw peas; mix together, then add 1/2 cup sour cream and 1 cup prepared Ranch dressing.
Combine and chill.

title: amish crock-pot stew
directions: Cooking Time: 9 to 10 hours.

title: beef upside down pie
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, paprika, celery salt and pepper; add 3 tablespoons shortening and mix thoroughly with fork.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons shortening in 9-inch frying pan and cook onion until soft.
Add tomato soup, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and ground meat.
Bring to boil.
Spread baking powder mixture on top of meat mixture and bake in hot oven at 475° for about 20 minutes.
Turn out upside down on large plate.
Serves 8.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix together.
Cook for about 10 minutes at 350°.
Crush one tube of Ritz crackers and cover with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake for additional 10 minutes.

title: fresh corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and lightly grease 12 muffin cups.
Sift together dry ingredients; mix in cornmeal.
In a separate bowl, combine beaten egg with buttermilk, margarine and corn.
Mix these ingredients with dry ingredients just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until done.

title: lazy sunday casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and onion in casserole.
Mix flour and crumbs.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours or until tender.
If too thick, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water. Serve with noodles, rice or potatoes.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Boil last 3 ingredients 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn and bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir about every 15 minutes.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder together; spread in a pie plate.
Top with pizza sauce, pepperoni, onion and green pepper.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Add the Mozzarella cheese; bake for 5 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Add extra flour to knead dough.
Roll out on floured board; cut into biscuits.
Brush with melted butter, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for several days.
Always allow biscuits to rise before baking.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Mix balance of cake mix with 1/2 stick margarine and 1 egg. Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes in
a 400° oven.
Mix together pumpkin, 3 eggs, 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Pour over baked cake mixture. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix together 1 cup cake mix, 1/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons margarine and nuts. Bake 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean at 325°.
Cool. Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except spinach.
Once blended, add drained and squeezed spinach.
Serve warm with bread, crackers and raw vegetables.

title: crouton stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes.
Scoop out pulp and sprinkle shells with salt.
Invert on paper towels to drain.
Strain pulp and save 6 teaspoons of the liquid.
Cook bread in oil until lightly browned.
Add cheese, basil, garlic, pepper and sugar.
Toss gently to blend.
Spoon mixture into tomatoes.
Pour liquid over. Place close together in shallow baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken wings.
Cut off tip of the wings.
Rub with salt; lay in a flat pan.
Rub or sprinkle with brown sugar.
Put all flavor barbecue sauce over each wing.
Put in a 350° oven; cook until brown.
Take out of oven; wrap in tinfoil and then put it back in oven for an additional 20 or 30 minutes.

title: baked tomatoes(french)
directions: Core tomatoes.
Cut in half horizontally.
Gently squeeze tomato halves to remove juice and seeds.
Sprinkle the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish lightly with salt.
Place tomatoes, cut side up, in the dish.
Drizzle with oil.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cut into small pieces. Cook rice.
Mix rice with Mexicorn and soup.
Spoon over chicken pieces.
Smooth and sprinkle cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Blend Oreos in blender; mix well with melted margarine (save 1/2 cup for topping).
Press remaining cookie mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese with 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread this mixture over the cookie crumbs.
Mix the milk with the instant pudding.
Spread this mixture over the cheese mixture.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding and sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: buttered coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and butter.
Sift into this mixture the salt and flour.
Add eggs and blend.
While blending, add water and vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 35 minutes on middle rack.
Lower rack to lowest point and bake additional 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 2-quart baking dish.

title: helen sabottke's cheese
directions: Mix and form into one or two balls.
Wrap in Saran. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on pedestal dish.
Pour Major Grey's chutney over top - 3 stalks finely chopped green onion (or use fresh chives).

title: beef burgundy
directions: Slice and saute onions in oil until golden brown.
Remove from pan and reserve for later.
Brown beef in small portions.
When all pieces are browned, stir in flour.
Add wine and 3/4 of the broth, salt, pepper, thyme and marjoram.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Then add onions and mushrooms.
Cook for 1 hour over medium heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Then mix sour cream, cream cheese, taco seasoning, bean dip and onions.
Divide in half and place half in a baking dish.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve on sliced avocado arranged on leaves of lettuce or your favorite salad.
Makes 1 cup.

title: harriet's fruit punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice, 1/2 the red grape juice and all the lemonade mix together.
Makes one punch bowl full.
Add ice ring. Great for showers and parties.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Arrange broccoli in bottom of a greased 7 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Combine other ingredients except onions.
Stir in 1/2 can of onions.
Pour mixture over the broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining onions over top.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry pineapple dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add pineapple and strawberries, nuts and marshmallows.
Pour in dish and chill.
Whip Dream Whip and cream cheese and pour on top.
Refrigerate.

title: squash pancakes
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Stir in flour.
Fry pancakes in hot oil, turning to brown on both sides.

title: traditional cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 13x9 inch baking dish or pan. In small skillet, cook and stir onion and celery in butter until tender.
In large bowl, combine cooked celery mixture, cornbread, bread, sage, and black pepper.
Mix well.
Add broth and eggs to cornbread mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 servings.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter with electric mixer until smooth. Slowly add sugar with spoon until a firm dough forms.
Add the Rice Krispies.
Form into egg shapes and refrigerate overnight.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Spread layer of brownie pieces into bottom of a glass serving bowl.
Spread a layer of pudding on top of the brownies.
Sprinkle pudding with candy bits.
Top with another layer of brownies.
Add another layer of pudding and candy bits.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with more candy bits as a garnish.
Serves 12.

title: play glue
directions: Will keep fresh in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: texas bundt cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Place everything in mixing bowl at once and beat for 10 minutes.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve plain or glazed.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix well and make crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon ice cubes
directions: Combine lemon juice, water and pineapple juice.
Pour into ice trays; freeze.
Use these with iced tea, lemonade, carbonated beverages and Cranberry/Orange Punch (recipe in this book).
Makes about 2 to 2 1/2 dozen ice cubes.

title: elaine's polish stew
directions: Slice onion, celery, carrots and potatoes into chunks.
Cook onion, celery and carrots until tender; add potatoes, cabbage, tomatoes and sausage.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for a while.

title: lasagne
directions: In hot oil in a heavy saucepan (use your large spaghetti pot), brown garlic and beef.
Cook and stir until crumbly, about like spaghetti.
Add salt, pepper, sweet basil, parsley, Parmesan cheese and tomato paste blended with hot water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: beef roast
directions: Bake at 300° for 6 hours.
Serve on buns.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Drain juice from can of crushed pineapple. Substitute juice for water called for in directions on cake box. If not enough, add water to make right amount. Follow directions for cake. Cool. Mix together cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk; spread over cooled cake. Combine whipped topping and drained pineapple; spread over pudding mixture.

title: tomato, broccoli chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with basil.
In large skillet, melt margarine over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 2 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet, reserving drippings.
In same skillet, saute Rice-A-Roni as package directs.
Add 2 1/2 cups water, special seasonings and chicken.
Bring to boil. Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand for 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pine-applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve each package of gelatin separately in 1 cup hot water, cool.
Stir pineapple and lemon juice into lemon gelatin; pour into 7 1/2 x 12-inch dish of pan and set aside to chill.
Mix strawberry gelatin with applesauce, cool but do not chill.
When pineapple layer is firm, carefully spoon applesauce layer over it. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: dill devil eggs
directions: Boil eggs. Scoop out yellow part of egg. Mash yolks. Add miracle whip, onion, dill relish and pepper. Mix well. Spoon into the egg whites. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Combine 1 cup of brown sugar, butter and 1/4 cup of milk and heat, stirring constantly, until a small amount forms a hard ball when tested in cold water. Heat remaining milk and stir into syrup gradually. Cool. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cream shortening with remaining sugar and vanilla. Beat eggs until light and add creamed mixture gradually, beating thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and butterscotch mixture alternately. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes one 10 x 10-inch cake.

title: cherry chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix oil, egg yolks, cherry juice, water and vanilla; add sifted ingredients.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten egg whites, gently folding in 1/2 cup very finely chopped and well-drained maraschino cherries and 1/2 cup finely chopped nut meats.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes.
When done, turn upside-down, free of table. Cool.
Loosen with spatula.
Ice with any good white icing.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine and mix with other ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake about 30 minutes at 375° (until firm in the middle and slightly brown on top).

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until hot and ready to eat.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake 1 hour in bread pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Brown ground meat (ground turkey may be used) in skillet.
Mix ingredients in order given:
black-eyed peas, cooked rice, tomatoes, cheese, onion, butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Add green chilies, if desired.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
I usually top with more cheese.

title: gumbo
directions: In a 3-quart pot over medium-high heat, make a roux by adding oil, then flour, stirring constantly.
Brown flour to a very dark brown, almost burning.
Add garlic, bell pepper and onion.
Turn down heat; saute until tender.
Add chicken broth, okra, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, hot sauce and salt.
Heat until boiling.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
Add meat and bay leaves.
If using seafood or smoked sausage, add raw and cook until done.
If using chicken or turkey, add 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Heat thoroughly.
Add water as needed to keep gumbo to a thin consistency.
Serve over rice with crackers. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Cook and stir until it comes to a boil.
Boil and stir for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: potatoes and pork chops
directions: Flour and brown chops.
Parboil potatoes for 15 minutes. Combine soup, milk and mustard; blend well.
Place potatoes in a buttered dish.
Top with chops and pour soup mixture over chops. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour; uncover the last 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Make in balls and roll in white sugar.
Takes 5 to 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take out of oven.
Put kisses on and return to oven for a couple of minutes.

title: jim's famous barbecue catalina chicken
directions: Dust chicken with butter and put on hot grill.	After about 3 or 5 minutes, pour Catalina salad dressing straight from the bottle on the chicken and turn chicken on the grill.
Pour dressing on the other side of the chicken and continue to turn to keep from burning.	Completely bake the chicken for about 12 minutes.
Remove from grill and add additional sauce if needed.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel, cube and boil potato.
Drain and mash in a medium size bowl.
Gradually add sugar.
Add and mix until you get a ball that does not stick to your fingers.
Sugar the table and roll to about 1/8-inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter.
Using a butter knife, slide under longest side and roll.
When all rolled, slice with a sharp knife and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove skin and bones. Wilt onion and pepper in skillet.
(Do not cook liver and gizzard with chicken.)
Add large package of noodles to broth and cook until done. Grate cheese and cut up pimento.
Put in large casserole dish a layer of noodles, layer of cut up chicken, layer of onion, pepper and pimento.
Put diluted soup over these. Sprinkle grated cheese. Repeat second layer.
Cook about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: casserole sauce
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
To make sauce, use 1/3 cup of mixture and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook until thickened.
Equal to one can of canned soup.
Good to use in place of canned soups in recipes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with mixer until blended well. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: mushroom round steak
directions: In a large plastic bag, combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Add beef, a few pieces at a time, and shake to coat.
In a large skillet, brown the beef in batches in oil.
Transfer meat to a slow cooker with a slotted spoon.
In a bowl, combine the soup, mushrooms, water, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove beef with a slotted spoon; keep warm.
Transfer cooking liquid to a saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and cold water until smooth; gradually stir into cooking liquid.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir a small amount of hot liquid into sour cream.
Return all to the pan; cook on low until heated through.
Serve over meat.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: vitamin cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Cover.
Blend until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Good reheated as a soup.

title: bean soup
directions: Place drained beans, broth and water in a 4 to 5-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, 40 minutes.
Skim foam off top.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine yams, seasonings, butter and brown sugar.
Crush Rice Krispies on piece of waxed paper.
Roll yam mixture into balls using about 1/3 cup for each ball.
Roll balls in Rice Krispies. Put maraschino cherry on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Can use either red or green cherries.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add sugar and jello.
Cool.
Crush the vanilla wafers; mix with 1/4 pound melted butter.
Set aside. Chill the can of milk; whip until stiff.
Fold into cooled pineapple mixture.
Line a glass baking dish with 1/2 crumb mixture.
Pour in pineapple mixture.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Chill and serve.!

title: rhubarb strawberry preserves
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: garlic bread
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Add onion and garlic.
Cut bread diagonally in 1-inch slices almost to the crust.
Spread slices and butter.
Wrap in foil.
Heat in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Whip egg white and water.
Stir in nuts so nuts are coated.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon.

title: dill pickled okra
directions: Use small, tender okra.
Cut with stems on.
